registry/assessments/l3a-parse.json:36:    "what_this_fail_establishes": "Three separable findings, each MEASURED at the frozen scope. (1) THE KERNEL'S OWN CLOSED GRAMMAR IS DECIDABLE, EXACTLY — the honest positive. The gold-replication arm reproduced 527/527 in-scope covered-exact in-run (G2), byte-identical on the deterministic repeat, and the deranged-lexicon control collapsed to 0.0 (G5): the engine's decidability is real and the eval is genuinely answerable only under correct concept binding. Nothing in this FAIL touches the engine, the closed grammar, or the parent l3a instrument-adequacy PASS. (2) THE DETERMINISTIC NL FRONT-END DOES NOT REACH THAT GRAMMAR FROM NATURAL LANGUAGE — the decisive negative. 251/527 = 47.6% covered-exact through a1-hybrid, UB 0.5121, a FAIL by a wide margin (not a near-miss). The mechanistic driver is measured and stark: the label-verbatim stratum parses at 259/339 = 76.4% but the PARAPHRASE stratum parses at 0/261 = 0.0% — the single-label-per-concept mapper with a rule lemmatizer and no synonym table (design section 3 / FK-NLB-8) abstains on essentially any phrasing that does not carry the exact relation label, and the 60-item no-label synonym probe confirms this by construction (0/60 parse-ok). This is a STRUCTURAL ceiling of the deterministic training-free front-end as instantiated, not a tuning shortfall: 'natural language' means paraphrase, and paraphrase is where it dies. (3) THE FAILURE IS SAFE ON THE FAMILY/WORLD VERTICAL — mis-parses become refusals. Covered wrong 8/527 (LB 0.0086 < 0.02): the S2 dangerous-wrong KILL did not fire, so the fail-closed contract holds on the safety-critical direction. This is the load-bearing contrast with a5-nl (code vertical), where the analogous KILL DID fire (43/855, LB 0.0394) — same front-end, opposite fail-closed outcome, because on the family/world vertical the mapper is the sole concept-binding stage and a mis-mapped concept dies at the engine as a safe refusal (no concept aliasing, ASM-0146), whereas on the code vertical the frame layer's direction table can mis-parse into a valid-but-wrong answer. The l3a fail-closed contract is imperfect in the secondary sense (8 covered wrong + 11 controls answered leave holm_s1_pass and holm_s2_pass both false), but it never crosses into the dangerous-wrong regime.",
registry/assessments/l3a-parse.json:38:    "scope_envelope": "The envelope is the frozen extrapolation_envelope_verbatim, restated honestly. WHAT THIS FAIL ESTABLISHES: on the 7-family shape-recoverable in-scope slice of the closed kot-query/1 grammar (n=527, family/world vertical), the ONE pinned deterministic a1-hybrid front-end build does not retain 90% of gold-parse covered exactness from THESE blind held-out NL phrasings, and it indicts the frame stage. WHAT IT DOES NOT GENERALIZE TO: (a) it says nothing about the two shape-ambiguous families (unique-maker, made-lookup) beyond their descriptive partial-negative — MEASURED it: unique-maker 0/43 exact (43/43 refused, 0 wrong), made-lookup 8/30 exact (0 wrong); those 73 items are carved out and no whole-closed-grammar reachability claim survives; (b) NO other mapper, gazetteer, or frame build — this is an a1-hybrid-specific result and the pre-declared successor (FK-NLB-3) is an LLM-assisted parser, a DIFFERENT front-end class the kill routes investment to; (c) NO natural-user-distribution robustness claim (phrasings are agent-authored under a blind protocol, not sampled from users); NO other phrasing distribution, corpus, domain, language, or paraphrase-set-size scaling; (d) NO cross-vertical conjunction — a5-nl licenses the code vertical separately, and the two verdicts must never be pooled; (e) crucially, it does NOT indict the kernel, the engine, or the closed grammar — the gold path replicates perfectly, so this is a boundary/front-end result, not a decidability result. A scoped FAIL is not softened (47.6% with UB 0.51 is decisive) and not over-generalized (it kills the a1-hybrid front-end at this slice, not the NL boundary in principle).",
