registry/assessments/l3a-parse-recoverability.json:25:  "rescope_decision": "l3a-parse RE-SCOPES to the shape-recoverable covered set: drop unique-maker (43) and made-lookup (30) from the SCORED covered set; primary/S2 denominators become n=527 over 7 families; the corpus, packets, phrasings, front-end, instrument and G2 ceiling arm stay byte-identical (scope applied in the pinned analysis script only). The dropped strata remain in the run and are reported DESCRIPTIVELY as a quarantined shape-ambiguous stratum — the finding stands as evidence; the instrument stops gating on it. Registered as fork FK-NLB-10 [STIPULATED: ASM-0420]; audit gate split shape+entity-gated / rel-label-descriptive [STIPULATED: ASM-0421]; audit extension without judge re-roll [STIPULATED: ASM-0422]; post-data scorer-side edit lawfulness boundary [STIPULATED: ASM-0424]. Full mechanics + recomputed decidability table: design doc section 14 (docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md).",
registry/assessments/l3a-parse-recoverability.json:30:  "adjudication": "DESIGN ARTIFACT of the lint rule, remedied by the NARROW EXEMPTION, not by dropping items. Chosen remedy: FK-NLB-11 [STIPULATED: ASM-0423] — EVAL-NO-ANSWER exempts a leak iff, after masking all occurrences of the item's entity surfaces (longest-first), no answer surface remains in the phrasing; exempted qids are DISCLOSED in a new receipt field (waived_forced_substring), never silently. Rejected: (i) dropping the 28 — they are NL-faithful and answerable, and they are systematically the ONLY items covering nested-definition and self-recursion semantics; dropping them would let a hygiene rule aimed at surface-reading arms delete a real semantic slice from an instrument no current arm can exploit (the deterministic pipeline extracts no answers from surfaces; the answer-all fabrication policy is surface-blind); (ii) accept-as-disclosed with a RED receipt — G3 gates on green; a permanently red gate is a dead gate. MANDATORY REUSE CAVEAT registered with the exemption: any successor with a model-based arm (a5-llm re-freeze) MUST exclude or re-phrase the waived qids — an LLM can read the answer off the question; the caveat rides in the a5-nl record's successors field and in ASM-0423. The EVAL-DIVERSITY finding needs NO decision: EVAL-BUILD-SPEC step 4 already prescribes fresh-identity re-authoring of the affected family; the coordinator executes it as written."
