registry/assumptions.jsonl:28:{"id": "ASM-0026", "claim": "The NL-boundary leg is pre-registered under record topology FK-NLB-1 option (b): TWO records (l3a-parse, a5-nl), TWO per-vertical verdicts, ONE shared harness whose files are pinned byte-identically in both records. Each vertical's kill (HL3a clause 2 / its HA5 analog) can fire independently, and no cross-vertical pooled average may stand in for a per-vertical verdict. This record topology is a methodology CHOICE of the programme: the frozen parents' per-vertical successor pre-declarations are its backing, but the two-record/one-harness execution shape is stipulated, not measured.", "tag": "STIPULATED", "backing_ref": "registry/experiments/l3a.json + registry/experiments/a5.json design.n_planned.successors (the frozen parents each pre-declare a SEPARATE successor id gated on their own verdict); docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 2 fork FK-NLB-1 + section 13", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "Two records let the parents' kill clauses fire independently - pooling verticals would smuggle a cross-vertical average into a per-vertical kill decision - while the shared harness (byte-identical pins in both records) keeps the instrument identical, so a cross-vertical difference indicts the vertical, not the tooling. Revisit condition: never while the parent records stay frozen (the FK-NLB-1 fork row is re-opens-never); if either parent record is ever superseded, the topology re-opens with its successor. Registered by the Fable designer role (nl-boundary line).", "resolution_path": "Not a projection to resolve: the stipulation lapses only if a frozen parent record is superseded; any consolidation into a single pooled record would be a NEW design record minting new ids, never an amendment of these two.", "notes": "FK-NLB-1 record-topology stipulation; cited by the section 13 DECISION line of docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md. Registered 2026-07-10 to close ERR_ASM_UNTAGGED_PREMISE on that line: a methodology decision is STIPULATED, not MEASURED - the parents' pre-declarations back it, they do not constitute it."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:76:{"id": "ASM-0222", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "The b-cov define-lane census is an EXPLORATORY, biomedical-skewed slice (OpenBookQA-test + 6 def-MMLU biomedical subjects, 1,550 items; WiC unmeasured, HTTP-401 data gap). Its MEASURED kappa_B^engine = 0.0000 characterises the external-benchmark end of the coverage gradient and is a MEASURED bound on efficiency-thesis BREADTH for the define lane on this slice, but it INFORMS without GATING the feasibility verdict: feasibility-synthesis.md section 4 rests the efficiency bottom line on de-confounding f2b (human f2b-transfer / K-NULL) and the correctness bottom line on the NL boundary (l3a-parse/a5-nl) + the g2/g3/g8/g9 semantics core, none of which this census touches.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/feasibility-synthesis.md sha 8c70cc64 section 4; registry/assessments/b-cov-define-lane.json (interpretation.efficiency_thesis_breadth_read); poc/b-cov-define-lane/census-summary.json sha 03f09f42", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "skeptic-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "A single exploratory, biomedical-skewed slice cannot move a cross-experiment feasibility verdict whose bottom lines rest on independent, untouched measurements; the honesty discipline is to record the 0.0000 as a breadth-substrate bound, not a verdict input. Revisit if a general/lexical (non-biomedical) external define census (e.g. WiC after the data unblock) reads out."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:85:{"id": "ASM-0140", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Agent-authored NL phrasings produced under the section-5 blind protocol of docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md (fresh authoring identities with no repo/lexicon/front-end/answer access, pinned prompts, committed transcripts, mechanical lints, recoverability audit) are an adequate held-out proxy for natural-language phrasings of the frozen l3a/a5 eval queries for the purpose of the NL-boundary records l3a-parse and a5-nl. Natural-user-distribution robustness claims are excluded from both extrapolation envelopes regardless of outcome.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md sections 5, 8, 10.1; registry/experiments/l3a-parse.json + a5-nl.json extrapolation_envelope_verbatim", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "No human phrasing panel is available at Tier 0; the blind protocol removes the tuning channels that could inflate or deflate the primary (authors never see what maps), and the residual shared-training-distribution risk is named in the design doc and carved out of the envelope rather than argued away.", "resolution_path": "A future human-authored phrasing set (or any externally sourced phrasing corpus for these queries) re-tests the same pinned pipeline; agreement retires this stipulation, disagreement bounds it."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:86:{"id": "ASM-0141", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "The pre-declared fraction in HL3a clause 2 (and its HA5 analog) is instantiated at 10% absolute maximum NL-boundary loss: primary floor 0.90 = measured gold ceiling 1.0 minus 0.10, for both l3a-parse and a5-nl. This is the programme's reachability POLICY level, not a measured quantity; an INCONCLUSIVE landing re-opens fork FK-NLB-2 with data.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md sections 2 (FK-NLB-2), 6.1; registry/experiments/l3a.json kill_criterion_verbatim (clause 2 verbatim)", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "Genuinely uncertain where reachable flips; 0.90 keeps the exactness premium the engine leg banked (>=9/10 covered NL queries answered exactly, every miss separately gated to be a refusal) while remaining decidable at both frozen n (P8 section-1.6 lint, design doc section 7).", "resolution_path": "The two records' verdicts measure against this floor; FK-NLB-2 re-opens it only via a new record id if the landing is INCONCLUSIVE."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:88:{"id": "ASM-0143", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "For the S1 control-refusal endpoint of l3a-parse/a5-nl, a front-end ERR_PARSE refusal is an ACCEPTABLE control outcome alongside the pre-authored expected engine code (FK-NLB-6): under an NL front-end a control may legitimately fail earlier in the pipeline (unknown entity -> gazetteer miss) than the engine stage the structured query would have reached. Conservative-direction note: this eases S1, but the dangerous direction (control ANSWERED, mis-parse answering wrongly) is separately gated by S2 and the control-answered count, and strict engine-code match is reported descriptively.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 2 (FK-NLB-6), section 6.2; registry/experiments/l3a-parse.json + a5-nl.json dependent_vars n_control_refused_acceptable", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "Fail-closed is the property under test; WHERE the pipeline refuses is instrument detail, WHETHER it answers a control is the safety property. Scoring strict engine-code equality would indict the pipeline for refusing too early, which is not a safety failure.", "resolution_path": "Never re-opened for this record pair; a successor caring about refusal-stage fidelity gates on the descriptively-reported strict rate."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:89:{"id": "ASM-0144", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "FK-NLB-8 (freeze-candidate fork, replaces the draft section-5 paraphrase quota): the draft's 'at most 50% of covered phrasings may contain the relation label verbatim' quota is REPLACED by (a) mechanically-linted syntactic-diversity quotas (>= min(6, n) distinct masked templates per covered family; no template > 50% of a family; canonical 'wh the <label> of <entity>' scaffold <= 50% per family), with free natural use of the relation's name, plus (b) a 60-item/vertical no-label synonym PROBE that is descriptive ONLY, never gated, and carved out of the envelope. Reason: the mapper lexicon carries exactly one label per concept and a rule lemmatizer with no synonym table, so no-label phrasings are unmappable BY CONSTRUCTION (measured probes: 'who gave birth to X' maps birth+give not mother; 'makers of'/'parts of' map nothing); a forced 50% no-label stratum would predetermine a FAIL arithmetically (0.5x1.0+0.5x~0 < 0.90) and make the primary undecidable at its planning value, violating the P8 section-1.6 lint the design binds itself to. The label-verbatim vs paraphrase stratification remains a reported endpoint, so residual label-use inflation is visible, not deniable.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md sections 2 (FK-NLB-8), 5, 10.1; mapper/src/lexicon.ts + mapper/src/lemmatize.ts (single-label lexicon, rule lemmatizer); tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_lint.py EVAL-DIVERSITY/EVAL-SCAFFOLD/PROBE-NO-LABEL", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "A gate that only a known-impossible synonym capability could pass measures nothing about the deterministic boundary under test; moving the synonym question to a never-gated probe measures the same direction honestly without manufacturing the verdict either way.", "resolution_path": "The probe's measured rates bound the synonym penalty; a parser-investment successor (FK-NLB-3 routing) with a synonym/alias layer would re-instate a gated paraphrase leg under a new record id."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:90:{"id": "ASM-0145", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "FK-NLB-9 (freeze-candidate fork, DEV-set re-basing): the DEV set used to finalise the frame layer is 60 designer-authored phrasings per vertical over FRESH minted identities (data/nlb-phrasings-*/dev-entities.jsonl) that are disjoint from every scored eval item and from both world stores (mechanically linted, DEV-FRESH), and DEV items are never scored in any arm; the DEV gazetteer augmentation (world entities + dev entities) exists only in the dev pass, never in a scored arm. Under this disjointness, designer authorship of DEV is admissible despite the designer having read the lexicon: the front-end is pinned BEFORE any EVAL phrasing exists, EVAL phrasings are authored blind by fresh identities, and a designer-DEV that fits the frame to unrepresentative phrasings can only LOWER the primary (the conservative direction) - there is no channel from DEV authorship to the blind EVAL distribution.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md sections 2 (FK-NLB-9), 5.3, 10.8; data/nlb-phrasings-l3a/manifest.json + data/nlb-phrasings-a5/manifest.json (authorship disclosure + ordering attestation); tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_lint.py DEV-FRESH", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "The draft protocol required disjoint AGENT identities for DEV; the coordinator-directed build strengthens the disjointness to the ITEM level (fresh entities, never scored) which is what actually blocks leakage into the primary, and it makes the DEV set buildable this pass without spawning authoring agents. G4 stays meaningful: it bounds front-end brokenness on phrasings the frame was ALLOWED to fit.", "resolution_path": "Standing for this record pair; the independent skeptic re-attack (build item 6) attacks it against the BUILT corpus before freeze."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:91:{"id": "ASM-0146", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "The frame layer's closed knowledge is part of the deterministic front-end under test and is legitimate NON-answer knowledge: the per-relation surface-orientation table (ROLE_DIR: which engine direction realises 'the R of E' per relation with world edges), the label-variant matcher over the mapped concept's OWN label (inflections + the two-irregular table made->make, children->child), the closed a5 op-keyword cascade, and the fail-closed op default (inverse-possessive shapes parse as lookup unless an exactly-one marker is present, because unique would GUESS cardinality and could fabricate a scalar answer). The frame layer performs NO concept aliasing: the mapper remains the sole concept-binding component, so a lexicon miss stays a mapper-abstain (clean stage indictment) and the G5 derangement of mapper bindings remains the scramble control for the whole semantic path.", "backing_ref": "tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_frontend.py (ROLE_DIR, _IRREG, _l3a_shape, _a5_op; sha 590377760ed5067688ddc0dd859c1a1cfa955e640b3a07c0f75e91d3bc908ea0 pinned in both records); docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 3", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "Some closed grammar-like knowledge is what a deterministic front-end IS; the registered line is that none of it may bind text to concepts (the mapper's job, scrambled by G5) or encode any eval answer. Orientation entries exist only for the five relations with world edges; every other relation defaults to a direction the engine refuses fail-closed.", "resolution_path": "Pinned; any extension (e.g. a synonym/alias layer after a FAIL) is the pre-declared parser-investment successor under a new record id."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:92:{"id": "ASM-0147", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Engine continuity for l3a-parse/a5-nl: tools/axiom/kot_axiom.py at the freeze-candidate pin (sha256 d26408815238cd9f73b50bb2c4b1f659c8a783ff6a5f16e27357eb2071bb3d08) is NOT byte-identical to the pin the frozen parents carry (d2064989c208c37df5a3d15a4fae6118c82516055fd6552f45a2a92fe2b7a659) because the define-op line extended the engine after the parents froze (additive define-op surface). The NL-boundary records rely on instrument gate G2 - the gold-replication arm must reproduce the parent-perfect outcome (600/600+300/300; 855/855+122/122) IN-RUN on the byte-identical parent evals/stores - as the behavioural-equivalence guard on the surface this experiment uses, instead of asserting byte-identity.", "backing_ref": "git commits fa210a6 + 9910052 (define-op engine extension); registry/experiments/l3a.json + a5.json harness pins (parent sha); poc/nlb-mock/l3a/mock-receipt.json + poc/nlb-mock/a5/mock-receipt.json gold_replication_parent_perfect=true (2026-07-10); registry/experiments/l3a-parse.json + a5-nl.json harness_manifest + verdict_rules (gold_replication_identical is a PASS conjunct)", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "rationale": "Restoring the old engine bytes would fork the shared module against the define-op line; the honest alternative is to pin what actually runs and make ceiling-reproduction an executable in-run gate (G2 is already a PASS conjunct and its failure is INSTRUMENT-INVALID), which is strictly stronger than an unchecked byte-identity claim about behaviour.", "resolution_path": "G2 in the final run re-verifies per run; if the engine is edited again before freeze, the records' pins must be re-stamped and the mock re-greened, else freeze is blocked."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:100:{"id": "ASM-0381", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "The review surface for each authored item is its NL gloss (concepts/<slug>.json gloss = review/sheets.json candidate_explication), stipulated as the faithful Minimal-English rendering of the kot-ast/1 explication AST. Gloss<->AST fidelity is authoring-asserted, NOT mechanically verified (no NL-realisation instrument exists in-repo). Conservative scoring direction stipulated: if the blinded review finds the gloss defective, the item scores as a composite FAIL for the authored arm - a gloss/AST divergence is an authoring defect of the arm under test, never grounds to re-score against the AST.", "backing_ref": "data/authored-explication-set/src/build.mjs (sheet construction); data/authored-explication-set/review/sheets.json _instructions", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "runner-10", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "Scored implicitly by g9.review (reviewers see only the gloss). A future NL-boundary instrument (l3a-parse/a5-nl lineage) could mechanise the fidelity check; until then this stipulation stands and is cited wherever the mechanical 50/50 is quoted.", "rationale": "Reviewers judge NL text while the encoder judges ASTs; the arm must be scored on what reviewers actually see, and the conservative direction prevents the authored arm from ever benefiting from its own rendering defects."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:111:{"id": "ASM-0420", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "FK-NLB-10 (l3a-parse shape-recoverable scope cut): the primary and S2 gated denominators of l3a-parse are the 527 covered items of the 7 shape-recoverable families (children-lookup 100, count-maker 43, instance-false-disjoint 40, instance-true 50, part-lookup 50, unique-father 122, unique-mother 122); unique-maker (43) and made-lookup (30) are excluded from every gate and reported as a descriptive quarantined shape-ambiguous stratum, carved out of the envelope. The exclusion is applied in the pinned analysis script only: corpus, packets, phrasings, front-end, instrument and the G2 gold-replication arm stay byte-identical, and controls stay at 270 with S1 unchanged. Precedent FK-NLB-5; here the absence of a shape-faithful NL rendering is MEASURED (blind round-trip shape recovery failed in exactly and only these covered families) rather than a priori.", "backing_ref": "data/nlb-phrasings-l3a/audit-recoverability.json sha256 d6365bd95e7d61a1cce7585bb446aa8f905b2b8eec08d0756a446e2e70a09bf5; registry/assessments/l3a-parse-recoverability.json; docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.2", "rationale": "English unmarked wh-questions are number-neutral and orientation-flexible for agentive noun relations, so the grammar's unique-vs-lookup and role-vs-flip distinctions on non-functional relations are not injectively recoverable from faithful natural phrasings; scoring them against exact gold shape lets phrasing underdetermination (not parser inadequacy) move the primary and can mechanically fire the S2 kill on semantically correct singleton answers (43 unique-maker items vs the 18/600 trigger). Dropping the strata records the measured partial-negative instead of letting it masquerade as a parser verdict. Revisit condition: a successor with marked-English phrasings or answer-shape-equivalence scoring (new record id) re-measures the dropped shapes.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:112:{"id": "ASM-0421", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB recoverability-audit gate split: the freeze-blocking gate is the SHAPE+ENTITY recovery rate over a 60-item covered-only in-scope sample, >= 0.95 (>= 57/60); relation/concept-label recovery and control-item recovery are reported descriptively and gate nothing. Applies to the l3a r1 audit and to the not-yet-run a5 audit (pre-data on that vertical).", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md sections 5.5 + 14.3; audit sha256 d6365bd95e7d61a1cce7585bb446aa8f905b2b8eec08d0756a446e2e70a09bf5 (rel_synonym_only_misses: 9/60 are shape+entity-correct)", "rationale": "The gate's registered purpose is answerability (a FAIL must not be manufacturable by unanswerable phrasings) and shape+entity carries exactly that; gating on label recovery under a stem-overlap rule forces label-verbatim authoring through the back door (re-imposing what FK-NLB-8 registered-removed) and double-counts the synonym penalty the experiment itself measures via the label-verbatim stratification and the never-gated probe; controls are insensitive to shape recovery in the dangerous direction because any parse of an out-of-scope or unknown item still refuses. Registered POST-DATA on the l3a vertical - disclosed as such; the independent skeptic re-attack must attack it as a forking-paths move before freeze.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:114:{"id": "ASM-0423", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "FK-NLB-11 (a5 forced-substring lint exemption): EVAL-NO-ANSWER masks all occurrences of the item's queried-entity surfaces (longest-first) out of the phrasing and flags only answer surfaces that survive masking; every exempted qid is disclosed in the receipt field waived_forced_substring. The 28 structurally self-naming a5 items (nested-function name prefixes: where-defined 9, contained-in 9; self-recursive call edges: callers-of 5, callees-of 5; verified 28/28 forced) STAY in the a5-nl scored set. MANDATORY REUSE CAVEAT: any successor with a model-based arm (a5-llm re-freeze) MUST exclude or re-phrase every waived qid, because a model can read the answer off the question surface; the caveat is written into the a5-nl record's successors field. l3a must re-lint green under the new rule with an EMPTY waived list.", "backing_ref": "data/nlb-phrasings-a5/lint-receipt.json sha256 da8c693da230f8dd6fdc75917ccbd40a476fcb28bddc5076ef477e64fda9acc8; data/nlb-phrasings-a5/eval.jsonl sha256 074b686cb5b0d8227c21f966f7c935e18fab002eb5d245033558e2321a5f1ba8; docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.4; ASM-0142", "rationale": "The leak is structural, not an authoring defect: the identifier is the entity's only name (ASM-0142) and the answer is a substring of it by the nested-naming/self-edge construction, so no faithful phrasing can avoid it. No arm in this record reads answers off surfaces (deterministic pipeline; surface-blind answer-all policy), the 28 items are the only coverage of nested-definition and self-recursion semantics, and the masked rule is exactly-scoped: any answer occurrence OUTSIDE the mandatory entity mention still flags. Dropping the items would delete a real semantic slice to satisfy a guard aimed at arms this record does not have; a permanently RED receipt would kill gate G3. Revisit condition: the reuse caveat re-opens as a blocking design question for any successor that adds a model arm.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:115:{"id": "ASM-0424", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB post-data edit boundary (pre-freeze design iteration lawfulness): the blindness invariant of the l3a-parse/a5-nl pair is carried by the FRONT-END artifacts and the committed phrasing bytes - nlb_frontend.py, nlb_map.mjs, the mapper a1-hybrid policy pin, and every phrasing in data/nlb-phrasings-* stay byte-untouched from the pre-EVAL pin (2026-07-10) through freeze. Scorer-side artifacts (nlb_lint.py, analysis/l3a_parse.py, analysis/a5_nl.py, the two DRAFT record JSONs) may change in this registered pre-freeze iteration in response to instrument-side findings, with new shas re-pinned in both records, because no scored outcome exists and the front-end cannot have adapted to the phrasings. The independent non-designer skeptic re-attack must explicitly attack ASM-0420..0425 as potential forking-paths moves, and the maintainer holds a veto at prereg-freeze.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md sections 5.3, 10.2, 14.5; registry/experiments/l3a-parse.json + a5-nl.json harness_manifest (front-end pins 590377760ed5067688ddc0dd859c1a1cfa955e640b3a07c0f75e91d3bc908ea0 unchanged)", "rationale": "The design's ordering protocol exists to prevent the front-end fitting the held-out phrasings; lint and analysis scripts neither parse nor answer, so amending them before any arm runs cannot leak eval content into the system under test, while refusing all post-data edits would leave a mechanically broken gate (RED G3 on structural non-defects) and a gate the re-scoped population cannot satisfy. Fail-closed boundary: any edit to a front-end artifact or phrasing byte after the pre-EVAL pin still mints a new record id, no exception registered.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:116:{"id": "ASM-0425", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Sizing/expectation note only: the l3a-parse primary planning value 0.95 is implausible - the audit sample measured natural-synonym phrasing on 9/27 = 0.333 of in-scope covered sampled items (count-maker 4/4, part-lookup 4/4, instance-true 1/4), and against the single-label mapper lexicon (no synonym table) those items are expected to abstain, putting the covered-exact rate plausibly in or below the 463-485/527 INCONCLUSIVE band (extrapolated from a 27-item audit sample to the 527-item scored set and from judge label-use to mapper parse behaviour - neither measured end-to-end). Used ONLY to set maintainer expectations that an INCONCLUSIVE/FAIL landing is live; never a premise for any gate, re-authoring, or re-design; the re-scope keeps every synonym-phrased item scored.", "backing_ref": "data/nlb-phrasings-l3a/audit-recoverability.json sha256 d6365bd95e7d61a1cce7585bb446aa8f905b2b8eec08d0756a446e2e70a09bf5 (rel_synonym_only_misses); docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.3", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "The l3a-parse run measures the covered-exact rate and the label-verbatim vs paraphrase stratification directly; whatever it returns supersedes this band. An INCONCLUSIVE landing re-opens FK-NLB-2 with data per ASM-0141; a FAIL routes to parser investment per the frozen kill text."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:124:{"id": "ASM-0480", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB scorer-enrichment lawfulness (extends the ASM-0424 lawful scorer-side edit set by exactly ONE named, diff-scoped edit): score_nl in tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_instrument.py gains four ADDITIVE per-family covered-outcome buckets in by_family - {exact, wrong, refused_parse, refused_engine} - each incremented on exactly the same branch as its existing run-level counterpart (n_covered_exact / n_covered_answered_wrong / n_covered_refused_parse / n_covered_refused_engine), zeros on control families, n and ok semantics unchanged: a pure re-bucketing of outcomes already classified AFTER the front-end has produced them. The blindness invariant is untouched: nlb_frontend.py, nlb_map.mjs, the mapper a1-hybrid policy pin and every phrasing byte stay byte-frozen; run_nl_arm, fabricate, oracle construction and the parse invocation are byte-unchanged; the doubled-pass determinism gate G6 compares outcomes, not metrics. The new sha 3d92e1ab7ef71ae577f63f8955f4381bc90a7c257e44102089220b96e25853d2 (supersedes pre-EVAL pin 426722aa813a7843190849348a6b309f3e898d19a0b979f354d5207dc85c6073) is re-pinned in BOTH DRAFT records' harness_manifest (l3a-parse + a5-nl; shared harness FK-NLB-1); analysis/a5_nl.py ignores the additive keys and stays unchanged. The edit is OUTCOME-INVARIANT: its schema is forced by the pre-diagnostic section-14.6 step-2 requirement (per-family wrong/refused for the FK-NLB-10 re-scope), not by the runner's disclosed post-audit diagnostic peek at mapper-parse outcomes (commit 0847ce079189b4d1244911fe026b0799e1db4da7, no committed artifact) - the same edit would be ratified whatever that diagnostic had shown. Any OTHER edit to nlb_instrument.py after the pre-EVAL pin still mints a new record id; the independent skeptic re-attack scope extends to this ASM and to the diagnostic disclosure.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.7; tools/experiments/nlb/nlb_instrument.py sha256 3d92e1ab7ef71ae577f63f8955f4381bc90a7c257e44102089220b96e25853d2; prior pin 426722aa813a7843190849348a6b309f3e898d19a0b979f354d5207dc85c6073; runner blocker + diagnostic disclosure commit 0847ce079189b4d1244911fe026b0799e1db4da7; verification: both green-mocks re-run under the enriched instrument with receipts byte-identical except wall-clock frontend_total_ns (poc/nlb-mock/l3a + poc/nlb-mock/a5, checks all green)", "rationale": "Section 14.6 step 2 needs the S2 numerator restricted to the 7 in-scope families and a descriptive per-family shape-ambiguous stratum; by_family {n, ok} carries exactness only, so neither quantity is derivable from the pinned emission plus run totals, and substituting the run-level total_wrong would silently rest on the contingent observation that the dropped families all abstained - exactly the manufactured-kill pathway section 14.1 preempts if that observation ever fails to hold on a re-run. Enriching the aggregation function is the minimal correct-by-construction alternative: score_nl neither parses nor answers, so amending it before any scored arm runs cannot leak eval content into the system under test (the ASM-0424 lawfulness basis, which enumerated the lint/analysis scripts but not the instrument aggregation function; this ASM closes that enumeration gap for this one edit and no other). Emitting raw per-qid outcomes instead was rejected as a larger surface change to the pinned kot-log/1 body; re-scoring inside the analysis script was rejected because the pinned analysis consumes record bodies only and must not re-run the pipeline. Fail-closed boundary: the permission is single-edit and diff-scoped, verified by the pinned sha pair; it does not open nlb_instrument.py to further amendment.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:165:{"id": "ASM-0620", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB post-outcome-registration disclosure (downgrades the outcome-blindness framing of ASM-0424/ASM-0480 for the l3a-parse/a5-nl pair): the 0847ce0 mapper-parse diagnostic disclosed scored-outcome information (the two FK-NLB-10 dropped families all abstained - unique-maker 43/43 refused, 0 wrong - and in-scope wrong = total wrong = 8) BEFORE the ASM-0480 enrichment ratification and the final scorer/record pins. Every scorer-side edit ratified after that commit (the ASM-0480 enrichment; the design-doc 14.8 round-2 hardening) is therefore POST-OUTCOME-DISCLOSED, and the pair's freeze is post-outcome registration with respect to those disclosed quantities. The previously claimed 'the same edit would be ratified under every possible outcome' counterfactual is WITHDRAWN as unenforceable and relied on nowhere. Lawfulness rests only on the disclosed terms: (i) the FK-NLB-10 carve-out and the enrichment schema requirement pre-date the diagnostic in the commit record (924bf6b before 0847ce0, independently confirmed by the round-2 skeptic); (ii) front-end, phrasing and eval bytes were pinned pre-diagnostic and are G7-enforced at analysis time; (iii) the pipeline is deterministic, so no selection-among-stochastic-outcomes channel exists; (iv) the independent skeptic re-attack gate and the maintainer veto remain the final control. Residual designer-knowledge risk is disclosed, not claimed zero.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md sections 14.5, 14.7, 14.8 item 1; poc/nlb-skeptic/skeptic-output.txt finding 1; commits 924bf6b + 0847ce079189b4d1244911fe026b0799e1db4da7", "rationale": "The independent round-2 skeptic showed the outcome-invariance claim was an after-the-fact stipulation, not an enforceable blind constraint; overclaiming an unenforceable constraint would be worse than disclosing the deviation. The register carries the honest epistemic status so the verdict layer and every consumer of these records see post-outcome registration, its bounded channels, and its remaining controls. Revisit condition: none for this pair; any future record wanting outcome-blind scorer amendment must pre-commit its amendment rule BEFORE any diagnostic runs (new ASM).", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:166:{"id": "ASM-0621", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB skeptic-round-2 scorer/lint hardening (extends the ASM-0424 lawful scorer-side edit set by exactly this named, diff-scoped edit set and no other, executed under the ASM-0620 post-outcome disclosure): (1) G0 one-row-per-arm in both pinned analysis scripts - duplicate/retry rows never resolve by log order; a re-run row must EXPLICITLY supersede every row it replaces via a top-level supersedes:[sha256 of the replaced body's sorted-keys JSON]; more than one non-superseded row per arm, or a dangling supersede target, is INSTRUMENT-INVALID in both log orders; (2) G7 harness-pin enforcement - the instrument-emitted pins_observed (engine, kot_code on a5, nlb_instrument.py, nlb_frontend.py, nlb_map.mjs, the parents' corpus digests, the phrasing corpus files eval/dev/dev-entities/probe/manifest, the lint receipt, the kot-corpus-hash/1 recipe string) must equal frozen constants byte-copied from the records on EVERY arm body, fail-closed on a missing pins block or any drift; (3) G5 existence - the deranged-lexicon arm must EXIST with well-formed integer counts over the full planned covered set before collapse is tested; a missing arm, empty metrics or absent n_covered_exact is a broken instrument, never 'perfect collapse'; (4) full counts integrity in BOTH scorers - run-level covered partition (exact+wrong+refused_parse+refused_engine == 600 l3a / 855 a5), run-level control partition (answered+acceptable+other == 270/106, refused_any == acceptable+other, acceptable == strict+parse on the mapper arm), family-key set equality with unexpected families rejected, per-family bucket partition + exact == ok, covered bucket sums == run-level twins, zero covered buckets on control families, non-negative-integer buckets; (5) nlb_lint.py defaults to --arms-profile model, under which a nonempty waived_forced_substring list is itself a blocking finding (green=False); --arms-profile deterministic-r0 is the explicit attestation pinned for this non-model pair, and the committed receipts regenerate byte-identically under it, so all corpus digests are unchanged. All edits are analysis/lint side; no front-end artifact or phrasing byte changes; no endpoint, threshold, or planned n moves.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.8 items 3-6 and 11; poc/nlb-skeptic/skeptic-output.txt findings 3-6 and 11 (findings 3, 5 and part of 6 empirically reproduced); analysis/l3a_parse.py + analysis/a5_nl.py --selftest fixtures covering each failure mode including the reproduced cases", "rationale": "The reproduced failures showed the previous scorers could admit order-dependent duplicate outcomes, treat an absent scramble control as perfect collapse, and accept mutually inconsistent count claims, while the emitted harness pins were prose rather than gates; each hardening converts a claimed invariant of design-doc sections 6.3/14.7 into an executable fail-closed check with a selftest fixture on the exact reproduced case. Revisit condition: a successor record with a model-based arm must re-derive its own lint-profile decision (the deterministic-r0 attestation is unlawful there per ASM-0423).", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:172:{"id": "ASM-0622", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB l3a audit r1 protocol, CORRECTED-COUNT SUCCESSOR of ASM-0422 (supersede-by-citation; the ASM-0422 line stands as append-only history and is no longer cited by the l3a-parse/a5-nl records): the protocol is unchanged - (i) mechanically re-score the COMMITTED judge transcript (sha256 7f3f2291a7e46fb554e7477fc92ff3611d4a0131e117aa5c027960563f36fb1a) restricted to the in-scope covered sampled items, (ii) top the covered-only sample to 60 via a FRESH judge identity given ONLY new in-scope items (same pinned prompt-audit.md, same deterministic sample rule over the 7 in-scope families, already-judged qids skipped), no item ever judged twice, original audit artifact never overwritten - but the provenance arithmetic in ASM-0422's rationale was wrong: the original committed audit sample contains 28 (not 27) in-scope covered items, so r1 = 28 mechanically re-scored + 32 (not 33) fresh-judge items. The 60/60 r1 gate result is unchanged.", "backing_ref": "data/nlb-phrasings-l3a/audit-recoverability-r1.json sha256 57e9d8d12826ae6ba28da4289fcc703109b2fb9994ef99eb589655874ea6da6d; original audit sha256 d6365bd95e7d61a1cce7585bb446aa8f905b2b8eec08d0756a446e2e70a09bf5; tools/experiments/nlb/EVAL-BUILD-SPEC.md step 5", "rationale": "The round-2 independent skeptic held (correctly) that an append-only register still CITED by live records must carry a mechanical superseding correction, not a prose disclaimer in the design doc: the 27+33 arithmetic in ASM-0422's rationale contradicts the committed r1 artifact (28 rescored + 32 fresh). This successor restates the identical no-re-roll protocol with the artifact's counts; both records now cite ASM-0622 in place of ASM-0422. Revisit condition: none for this pair; a successor audit protocol supersedes it with its own ASM.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:173:{"id": "ASM-0623", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Sizing/expectation note only, CORRECTED-COUNT SUCCESSOR of ASM-0425 (supersede-by-citation; the ASM-0425 line stands as append-only history and is no longer cited by the l3a-parse/a5-nl records): the l3a-parse primary planning value 0.95 is implausible - the audit sample measured natural-synonym phrasing on 9/28 = 0.3214 (not 9/27 = 0.333; the in-scope covered sample has 28 items per the committed r1 artifact) of in-scope covered sampled items (count-maker 4/4, part-lookup 4/4, instance-true 1/4), and against the single-label mapper lexicon (no synonym table) those items are expected to abstain, putting the covered-exact rate plausibly in or below the 463-485/527 INCONCLUSIVE band (extrapolated from a 28-item audit sample to the 527-item scored set and from judge label-use to mapper parse behaviour - neither measured end-to-end). Used ONLY to set maintainer expectations that an INCONCLUSIVE/FAIL landing is live; never a premise for any gate, re-authoring, or re-design; the re-scope keeps every synonym-phrased item scored.", "backing_ref": "data/nlb-phrasings-l3a/audit-recoverability-r1.json sha256 57e9d8d12826ae6ba28da4289fcc703109b2fb9994ef99eb589655874ea6da6d; docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md sections 14.3 and 14.9", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "The l3a-parse run measures the covered-exact rate and the label-verbatim vs paraphrase stratification directly; whatever it returns supersedes this band. An INCONCLUSIVE landing re-opens FK-NLB-2 with data per ASM-0141; a FAIL routes to parser investment per the frozen kill text."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:174:{"id": "ASM-0624", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB skeptic round-2 RE-AUDIT remediation (extends ASM-0621's lawful edit set by exactly this named, diff-scoped edit set and no other; SUPERSEDES ASM-0621 item (1)'s supersede mechanics, which the re-audit proved unexecutable in a kot-log/1 log): (1) kot-log/1 gains an executable run-row retry-supersession channel - a run row may carry supersedes:[row sha256,...], row identity = sha256 of the replaced results-log line's exact bytes incl. newline (identical to prev_sha256 / reuse.row_hashes identity); log-append enforces fail-closed: run-event only, mandatory non-empty reason, no duplicate targets, every target an EXISTING exit:'ok' run row of the SAME config.arm and phase not already superseded; self/forward/cyclic references are structurally impossible (a target must already be a chain line); event:'supersede' keeps refusing exit:'ok' targets, so a success is never voided WITHOUT its replacement row, and any retry remains in-chain and auditor-visible (result-shopping is additionally detectable via gate G6 determinism). (2) Both pinned scorers' G0 re-verify the SAME semantics independently: supersedes must be a non-empty list of distinct 64-hex row hashes, targets present among scored records, same-arm, non-self; malformed forms (dict/string), cross-arm supersession, byte-duplicate rows, records without a string config.arm (the top-level arm fallback is removed), dangling targets, arms with zero survivors, and >1 surviving row per arm are all INSTRUMENT-INVALID in every log order; verdict-gen passes eligible rows (including retry-superseded ok rows) unchanged to the pinned scorer, which is the resolution point. (3) The pinned instrument emits a DIRECTLY appendable kot-log/1 run body: event 'run', exit 'ok', phase from --phase, prereg_hash auto-stamped from registry/frozen-index.json post-freeze (absent pre-freeze so log-append refuses ERR_P2_NOT_FROZEN), no undeclared top-level key (the former top-level 'arm' is removed; config.arm is the only arm declaration), and native --supersedes/--reason flags for the retry path. (4) G1/G2/G4 counts hardening in both scorers: per-family control acceptable ('ok') sums must equal the run-level n_control_refused_acceptable; run-level totals n_covered/n_control/dev_n, dev_parse_refused, and every gold-replication counter must be strict non-negative integers; dev_parse_refused <= dev_n; G4 divides only well-formed in-range counters. (5) Honesty corrections carried in the same change: the instrument docstring no longer claims a byte-identical engine (G2 behavioural claim restated), and the section-14.8 item-7 'bit-equal' complement claim is softened to the measured fact (identical gate decision at every integer count; 4/527 differs by one binary64 ULP, 9/855 bit-equal). All edits are log-schema/log-writer/scorer/instrument-envelope side; no phrasing or eval byte, endpoint, threshold, decision boundary, or planned n moves.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.9; poc/nlb-skeptic/skeptic-round2-output.txt sha256 6e60f408a4231c595832dd6b91262ef49c3617a410e5e71522ea33bb578b7773 (attacks on the dict-valued and cross-arm supersedes, zeroed control-family ok, float totals and dev_parse_refused reproduced there); analysis/l3a_parse.py + analysis/a5_nl.py --selftest fixtures on each reproduced attack; scratch-log run-to-log integration demonstration via the real tools/registry/log-append.py", "rationale": "The round-2 re-audit proved the registered recovery path could not exist in a real hash-chained log (kot-log/1 additionalProperties:false rejects the field; log-append's supersede event cannot target ok rows; only ok rows reach the scorer), so freezing would have pinned an unexecutable protocol where one accidental duplicate append poisons the record permanently. Making the channel real in schema+writer+scorer, with append-time AND read-time enforcement of one registered rule, converts the promise into an executable, auditable mechanism while PRESERVING the anti-re-roll invariant (a successful row is only ever replaced by an explicit, reasoned, same-arm successor in the chain). The counts hardening closes the reproduced acceptance of contradictory control-family classifications and non-integral counters. Revisit condition: any change to kot-log/1 row identity or to canonical JSON serialization must re-derive the scorer's self-contained _row_sha twin.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:185:{"id": "ASM-0625", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB skeptic round-3 remediation (extends the ASM-0621/ASM-0624 lawful edit set by exactly this named, diff-scoped edit set and no other; design doc 14.10 items A+B): (1) G0 COMPLETED - both pinned scorers re-validate the FULL append-time retry-supersession semantics that are order-independently checkable at read time: a run row carrying supersedes must state a non-blank string reason (missing_reason detail), and no target may be retired twice, the order-free form of log-append's not-already-superseded rule (retired_twice detail); both INSTRUMENT-INVALID in every log order. The registered 'two independent enforcements of one registered rule' defence-in-depth claim is thereby made TRUE rather than downgraded (resolution (a) of the round-3 finding-1 options). Target event/exit/phase remain enforced TRANSITIVELY and are registered as such: verdict-gen's eligibility filter drops non-run/non-final/non-ok rows before the scorer, leaving any reference to them dangling (already G0-invalid). (2) G1 SHORT-CIRCUIT - any g1_counts failure returns immediately after the gate block with instrument_valid false, an EMPTY analysis block, valid-JSON stdout and exit 0, so verdict-gen's frozen rule 0 fires the registered INSTRUMENT-INVALID and no rejected denominator (boolean/float/negative/missing) ever reaches Wilson/Holm/descriptive arithmetic (previously n_control=True crashed both scorers into ERR_P2_ANALYSIS and a5 n_covered=True emitted unserializable complex Wilson values). (3) G1 additionally types every remaining analysis-divided counter (label_strata, synonym-probe counters, frontend_total_ns when present; in-range non-negative integers, bool excluded) and non-dict metrics/pins_observed bodies on any arm are handled fail-closed, never as exceptions. (4) Fixture-side only: Holm-boundary fixtures now construct an internally consistent control split (non-acceptable remainder deducted from by_family ok). All edits are scorer-side; no phrasing or eval byte, instrument sha, endpoint, threshold, decision boundary, or planned n moves.", "backing_ref": "docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.10; poc/nlb-skeptic/skeptic-round3-output.txt sha256 5d1867482fab9065233936d8080b36b251116040cea93707f57604c922babdde (missing/blank-reason and double-retirement acceptance plus the boolean-total crash paths reproduced there); analysis/l3a_parse.py sha256 d6b3e65e6206cd781713f54c529c4b70bf6e72141e741704011f341a80901ce6 + analysis/a5_nl.py sha256 4ea2383cc8c75c8d32a50c8229fe13550a478847906f80ddb07e9d0827cde018 --selftest fixtures on each reproduced attack", "rationale": "The round-3 re-audit proved two claim-vs-implementation gaps inside already-registered items: the scorer-side defence-in-depth claim of ASM-0624 item (2) enumerated fewer checks than the append path enforces (an overclaim reachable from a manually constructed, schema-valid chain), and the ASM-0624 item (4) counts promise classified malformed counts INSTRUMENT-INVALID only when the scorer survived to say so (boolean denominators crashed it into ERR_P2_ANALYSIS instead). Making the scorer re-validate reason + single-retirement makes the registered independence claim true at trivial cost; short-circuiting on G1 failure makes the registered verdict classification mechanically reachable on every malformed-count input. Revisit condition: any change to kot-log/1 supersession semantics or to the analysis-consumed metric surface must update G0/G1 in both scorers in the same change.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:186:{"id": "ASM-0626", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Freeze-tool pause-scan supersession resolution (design doc 14.10 item C): prereg-freeze.py scan_open_extrapolations resolves the register's supersede-by-citation convention mechanically - a current register entry whose claim carries the marker 'SUCCESSOR of ASM-NNNN (supersede-by-citation' retires the named predecessor from the live scan, and any citation of the predecessor (record bytes or pinned prereg doc, including supersession/historical prose) is followed along the supersession chain, cycle-safe, to its live end; the live entry is flagged iff it is itself an open EXTRAPOLATION. A historically-cited-but-superseded ASM therefore emits no live pause flag; on the l3a-parse/a5-nl records the flag set becomes exactly ASM-0623. PAUSE remains non-fatal either way (stop false conclusions, not experiments).", "backing_ref": "tools/registry/prereg-freeze.py (ASM_SUPERSEDED_RE + scan_open_extrapolations); docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md section 14.10 item C; registry/assumptions.jsonl ASM-0622/ASM-0623 (the marker's first uses, per section 14.9 item D); poc/nlb-skeptic/skeptic-round3-output.txt sha256 5d1867482fab9065233936d8080b36b251116040cea93707f57604c922babdde", "rationale": "The round-3 re-audit showed the dry-run pause flag for the superseded ASM-0425 contradicted the 14.9 item-D remediation claim that no live citation reaches the stale entry: the scanner treated every ASM token in the pinned doc as a live citation, including the supersession prose itself. Following the register's own supersede-by-citation marker keeps the register append-only, keeps historical prose intact, and makes the backlog signal point at the entry a resolution would actually retire (the successor), instead of a line nothing live rests on. Revisit condition: if the register ever gains a first-class machine-readable supersession field, the prose-marker recognition should be superseded by it in the same change.", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10"}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:191:{"id": "ASM-0720", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NL-boundary consumption discipline (operative discharge of the frozen kill routing for the l3a-parse / a5-nl FAIL pair; binding on every downstream citation of the deterministic NL front-end). MEASURED basis: the ONE pinned deterministic training-free front-end (mapper a1-hybrid policy sha e13dc838 + entity/identifier gazetteer + closed frame layer) is non-viable at the frozen 0.90 covered-exactness retention bar on BOTH NL-boundary verticals (l3a-parse 251/527 = 0.476, Wilson UB 0.512; a5-nl 356/855 = 0.416, Wilson UB 0.444), and on the CODE vertical it additionally breaks the fail-closed contract (a5-nl S2 dangerous-wrong KILL fired: covered wrong 43/855, Wilson LB 0.0394 >= 0.02), whereas on the FAMILY/WORLD vertical the fail-closed contract holds on the dangerous direction (l3a-parse S2 KILL absent: 8/527, LB 0.0086 < 0.02). Discipline: (1) no plan / prospectus / pitch / prereg premise may cite the deterministic a1-hybrid front-end as a working NL-to-kernel boundary at any bar at or above the tested 0.90 on either vertical; (2) the pre-declared parser-investment successor (FK-NLB-3: an LLM-assisted parser, or a deterministic synonym/frame-direction repair under a new record id) carries the re-entry per vertical, never more GPU (frozen kill routing verbatim); (3) the a5-nl fail-closed break is a binding SAFETY caveat for the code vertical specifically - a deterministic front-end on the code vertical emits confident wrong answers with provenance attached (frame ROLE_DIR orientation flips in contained-in / where-defined), so no code-vertical NL deployment or usefulness claim may rest on the front-end's fail-closed contract until a successor re-clears BOTH the exactness bar and the S2 gate; the a5-llm engine-vs-LLM PASS (formal gold-parsed inputs) is not retracted but its deployment/differentiator reading inherits this measured NL-boundary FAIL; (4) each FAIL binds ONLY its own vertical at its frozen slice (l3a family/world n=527 7-family shape-recoverable slice; a5 code n=855) - NO cross-vertical conjunction, and the per-vertical fail-closed outcomes (l3a safe, a5 dangerous) must never be pooled. This discipline restates and consumes MEASURED verdicts within their frozen scope; no generalization beyond scope is asserted.", "backing_ref": "registry/verdicts/l3a-parse.json (7b67bc54) + registry/verdicts/a5-nl.json (8e80a890) + registry/assessments/l3a-parse.json + registry/assessments/a5-nl.json", "rationale": "Mirrors the g9-llmproxy (ASM-0648) and truthstyle-2x2 (ASM-0680) consumption-discipline precedents: a scoped-but-decisive FAIL must be prevented from being silently dropped or, worse, cited as a non-result. Overclaiming a working (or safe) deterministic NL boundary from a double FAIL would be worse than pausing the claim; the frozen kill text already routes the consequence to parser investment, and the a5 fail-closed break makes the safety pause non-optional on the code vertical. The register carries the honest binding so the capstone synthesis and every consumer read the pair at exactly its frozen scope.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "The FK-NLB-3 parser successors (LLM-assisted parse and/or deterministic frame-direction / synonym repair, per vertical, new record ids) re-measure the 0.90 retention bar and the S2 fail-closed gate; whatever they return supersedes clauses (1)-(3) at their own scope. A successor PASS lifts the pause for that vertical and front-end class only."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:192:{"id": "ASM-0721", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Cross-experiment boundary-pattern reading (interpretive colour for the capstone synthesis; never a premise, load-bearing for nothing). The programme's measured correctness evidence is consistent with a single pattern: the kernel's deterministic machinery is sound ON ITS OWN CLOSED GRAMMAR / self-authored substrate - l3a-parse & a5-nl gold-replication identical (527/527 and 855/855 in-run, G2), g8 F/B round-trip 33/33 with live F-verification, parent engine exactness 100% on gold - but does NOT survive measured boundaries into real or natural input, on four distinct boundaries: (i) the natural-language input boundary (l3a-parse 47.6% / a5-nl 41.6%, both FAIL the 0.90 bar, a5-nl also breaking fail-closed); (ii) the wild-formal-content boundary (g8 fragment 0/1000 random Mathlib at kernel size 39, FAIL, cross-vendor CONFIRMED); (iii) the model-internal-computation boundary (nsk1 flagship INCONCLUSIVE - internal channel delivers at echo grade, integration into free generation unresolved at-or-below the content-free null); (iv) the compute-matched verifier-offload boundary (f2 FAIL - kernel-verifier arm did not dominate the text null / gloss-self-verify at matched budget). g7 is a formalism-capacity design selection (kot-ast/2), not a boundary result; g9-llmproxy is an early-warning FAIL-analog (authoring lane, claims paused); the one neighbouring PASS, truthstyle-2x2, is an INSTRUMENT-adequacy result (LLM-judge endorsement not materially style-leaky at margin 0.10) that makes other readings trustworthy, not a kernel-content win. The NL-boundary pair adds a reachability axis on top of the coverage axis (g8/m0b/compression-census measure whether the kernel CONTAINS the target; l3a-parse/a5-nl measure that even content the kernel DOES contain and CAN decide perfectly under gold parse is not reliably ADDRESSABLE from natural language through the pinned deterministic front-end). This is a DIRECTION reading over heterogeneous experiments with DISJOINT envelopes; it is NOT a measured cross-experiment quantity, aggregates nothing, and may never serve as a premise, prereg motivation-as-fact, or pitch claim.", "backing_ref": "registry/verdicts/l3a-parse.json + registry/verdicts/a5-nl.json + registry/verdicts/g8.json + registry/assessments/nsk1-stage1.json + registry/verdicts/f2.json + registry/assessments/truthstyle-2x2.json (each figure index-bound to its own verdict's envelope)", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-10", "resolution_path": "Each boundary has its own pre-registered successor: FK-NLB-3 LLM-assisted / deterministic-repair parsers (NL boundary, per vertical); g8 bulk-authoring regression + ntp-toolkit definiens leg (coverage/formal boundary); nsk1 integration successors (model-internal boundary); f2 successors (verifier-offload boundary). The pattern is confirmed or broken ONLY by those successors landing, never by aggregating the current heterogeneous negatives."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:195:{"id": "ASM-0760", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Capstone feasibility verdicts (Fable, 2026-07-11; the programme-completion-loop 'Done' conclusion, docs/next/feasibility-synthesis.md). CORRECTNESS thesis = INCONCLUSIVE-PENDING (a) an NL-reaching parser FK-NLB-3 and (b) the semantics core (g2 Pi-soundness vs blind human gold, g3 necessity), within SCOPE {kernel-v0/molecules-v0 instance, R0-1.7B hosts, family/world + code verticals, the one pinned a1-hybrid deterministic front-end, self-authored covered slice}; the instrument sub-claim (a sound, fail-closed, provenance-carrying, microsecond deterministic checker EXISTS and ports across verticals with a byte-identical engine) is FEASIBLE-and-DEMONSTRATED but INSTRUMENT-ONLY, and every MEASURED crossing into real/natural input is negative so far (l3a-parse FAIL safe, a5-nl FAIL dangerous, g8 FAIL, nsk1 INCONCLUSIVE); CONFIDENCE high on instrument + current-build boundary negatives, thesis-level INCONCLUSIVE because the two decisive legs are unrun not failed. EFFICIENCY thesis = INCONCLUSIVE-PENDING (a) de-confounding the one end-task positive (knull K-NULL aligned-non-NSM ablation OR human f2b-transfer Stage-1), (b) mint-cost (A-F0 key-gated unrun), (c) the A-E2 consumption channel (K-A3/K-A4 unmeasured), within SCOPE {<=1.7B hosts, self-authored covered/formal slice, one PRM size class, 10k-concept census anchor}; a real audited verifier-offload SIGN exists on FORMAL inputs (f2b-replicate +0.1507 at ~10% FLOPs) but is correct-ALIGNMENT-specific not shown kernel-content-specific, and the A-E2 compression figure is a MEMBERSHIP UPPER BOUND never achievable savings; CONFIDENCE high on all three. Neither thesis is dead; neither is established.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/feasibility-synthesis.md sections 1-2 and 6; registry/verdicts/{l3a,a5,l3a-parse,a5-nl,g8,f2b-replicate,f2b-transfer-llmproxy,f2,f1,truthstyle-2x2,m0a-llmproxy,g9-llmproxy,m0b,a5-llm}.json; registry/assessments/{a-e2-census,f2b-replicate,oracle-coverage,f-efficiency,nsk1-stage1,nsk1-g2d,nsk1-bprime2}.json", "rationale": "The GOAL deliverable is a defensible per-thesis feasibility verdict within honest envelopes; both resolve to INCONCLUSIVE-PENDING because the decisive legs (semantics core; the de-confound of the one positive) are unrun and human/input/key-blocked, while the measured evidence is strong on the instrument half and on the boundary negatives.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "resolution_path": "CORRECTNESS resolves when FK-NLB-3 (NL boundary) and g2/g3 (semantics core, human-gold gated) read out; EFFICIENCY resolves when the knull K-NULL ablation (after its plain-control rewrite) or human f2b-transfer Stage-1 de-confounds the +0.1507, and A-F0 + an A-E2 consumption measurement price the compression side."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:197:{"id": "ASM-0762", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "Cross-thesis reachability-wall-on-coverage-wall reading (interpretive colour for the capstone; NEVER a premise, load-bearing for nothing; extends ASM-0721 to the efficiency thesis). The programme's measured evidence across BOTH theses is consistent with one shape: the kernel's deterministic machinery is exact and sound INSIDE its own closed grammar / self-authored substrate (l3a/a5 gold-replication identical 527/527 and 855/855; g8 F/B round-trip 33/33; engine exactness 100% on gold), while there is a COVERAGE wall (does the kernel contain the target: g8 0/1000 random Mathlib, m0b 0.3542 friendliest corpus, compression-census ~0.6% roll-up engagement, b-cov-define-lane 0/1550 external items) and, stacked on it, a REACHABILITY wall (even for content the kernel DOES contain and CAN decide perfectly under gold parse, natural language cannot reliably ADDRESS it through the pinned a1-hybrid front-end: l3a-parse 47.6%, a5-nl 41.6%). The one audited efficiency positive (f2b +0.1507) lives strictly inside the fortress (formal, self-authored, alignment-specific), and the neighbouring PASS (truthstyle-2x2) is instrument-adequacy not kernel content. Each constituent figure is index-bound to its own verdict's envelope; the conjunction is direction-only and is confirmed or broken only by the pre-registered per-boundary successors.", "backing_ref": "registry/assessments/{l3a-parse,a5-nl,g8,oracle-coverage,compression-census,b-cov-define-lane,a-e2-census,f2b-replicate,truthstyle-2x2}.json; registry/verdicts/{l3a-parse,a5-nl,g8,m0b,f2b-replicate,truthstyle-2x2}.json; ASM-0721", "rationale": "The pattern is the most consistent thing the registry shows and is worth stating for the maintainer, but it aggregates figures across incommensurable envelopes, so it must remain EXTRAPOLATION and may never premise any verdict.", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "resolution_path": "Each boundary is confirmed or broken by its own pre-registered successor (FK-NLB-3 for the NL wall; the bulk-authoring re-entry for the wild-formal wall; nsk1 Stage-1+ for the model-internal channel); the reading dissolves into per-boundary MEASURED facts as those land."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:202:{"id": "ASM-0800", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Programme-3 north-star operationalisation (design/goal choice, not evidence). (1) 'AI index' := KOT-AI-INDEX/1 — a versioned, pinned macro-average over a fixed benchmark suite evaluated ONLY under the programme's own pinned harness (own-harness numbers are the comparator; published card numbers are anchors only): at rungs R-0..R-2 the SmolLM2-anchor suite (HellaSwag, ARC-E/C, PIQA, MMLU-cloze, CommonsenseQA, WinoGrande, OpenBookQA, GSM8K; TriviaQA licence-gated) per docs/next/benchmark-evaluation-strategy.md section 1.1; at R-3+ the suite extends with MMLU-Pro, BBH, and one code benchmark, as a NEW index version. (2) 'size' := KOT-SIZE/1 — raw on-disk bytes of the complete frozen deployment artifact needed to serve the eval (weights as serialized at their stored precision + kernel store + world-layer + indices + GNN/adapter/rule components + tokenizer + all non-base-image code), measured against a pinned common base image; zstd-19 bytes co-reported. (3) 'inference cost' := KOT-COST/1 — dual ledger: analytic FLOPs/query for neural components AND measured wall-clock + peak RSS + energy per query on pinned hardware for the WHOLE system including symbolic components; a compute-matched claim must hold on BOTH ledgers. (4) Win condition W1 and shrink objective W2 as stated verbatim in docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md section 1.4.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md section 1", "rationale": "The maintainer's goal ('higher AI index than all models of same size and compute; then minimise size') is not measurable until 'AI index', 'size', and 'compute' are pinned. These are design choices: the SmolLM2 suite is chosen because the programme's host family publishes against it and the harness-pinning design already exists (benchmark-evaluation-strategy.md); on-disk bytes is chosen because parameters cannot measure a neurosymbolic system's size (maintainer directive); the dual cost ledger is chosen because symbolic operations have no canonical FLOP equivalent.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Programme-3 design doc. Any change to the suite, size recipe, or ledger is an index/recipe VERSION change and re-baselines every comparison."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:203:{"id": "ASM-0801", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Programme-3 fair-comparison protocol (design choice). (1) Baseline ladder: published card numbers = anchors only, never comparators; own-harness re-evaluations of open pure-neural models in the same KOT-SIZE/1 band (+/-10 percent bytes) = the PRIMARY comparator; training-compute-matched from-scratch neural baselines = required comparator only at rungs where the neurosymbolic arm itself trains from scratch. (2) 'Same compute' binds on INFERENCE compute (both KOT-COST/1 ledgers); training compute is always reported and is enforced as matched only at ground-up rungs. (3) Mandatory control set for ANY claimed neurosymbolic win: kernel-as-text null, seed-pinned deranged-store control, aligned-non-kernel-store control (the knull lesson), and a benchmark-decontamination audit of kernel+world store vs eval items (n-gram + embedding screen) — a win that fails decontamination is void, not caveated.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md section 2", "rationale": "f2b-replicate demonstrated that an end-task lift can be correct-alignment-specific rather than content-specific, and l3a/a5 demonstrated that published-vs-own-harness comparisons are non-comparable across variant/harness cells; the protocol mechanises those two lessons before any Programme-3 number exists. Inference-compute-primacy is chosen because the maintainer's objective is a deployed-system property.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Inherits the mandatory-controls discipline from kot-reg/1. The decontamination audit is new to Programme-3 because the kernel/world store, unlike weights, can trivially embed benchmark answer keys."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:204:{"id": "ASM-0802", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Programme-3 architecture design-space enumeration and naming (scoping decision): the candidate families are H-VL (verifier-loop system, external), H-GNN-{ST,KV,LF} (graph-encoder fusion via soft-tokens, KV-side memory, or late fusion), H-RULE-{CD,KV,AD,ACT,HL} (rules inference at constrained-decoding, KV-side, adapter, activation-steering, or dedicated-hidden-layer placement), H-RB (retrieve-vs-bake store placement fork), H-GU (ground-up neurosymbolic training), and H-DD (dimension-drop of an existing model). The enumeration claims coverage of the maintainer's directed directions plus the seams Programme-2 already built; it does NOT claim any family works — each carries only the evidence its cited verdicts license, and several start from measured negatives.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md section 3", "rationale": "A finite named hypothesis list is required so lit-reviews, design tasks, and kill criteria attach to stable identifiers; naming is a scoping choice that creates no evidence. Families are seeded from the maintainer's brief (GNN, rules-in-LLM, ground-up vs dimension-drop) and from the L0-L4 ladder already designed in docs/next/architecture-ladder.md.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Any additional family found by Phase-0 lit reviews is appended as H-* by a Phase-1 design task, not silently merged."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:205:{"id": "ASM-0803", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Programme-3 scaling ladder (design choice): rungs R-0 (1-30M params-equivalent, synthetic/TinyStories-class data, CPU or single free GPU), R-1 (100-200M, SmolLM2-135M anchor), R-2 (300-500M, SmolLM2-360M anchor), R-3 (1-2B, SmolLM2-1.7B anchor), R-4 (3-8B, gated). Promotion gate: an architecture family may occupy rung R-(k+1) only if at rung R-k it (a) beat its matched control set on the rung's pre-registered primary endpoint or (b) was explicitly promoted by a maintainer fork overriding a diagnosed instrument failure. Kill: a family that fails its primary at two consecutive rungs, or whose R-0/R-1 falsifier fires, is closed at scope. Real-GPU spend above the free-credit pool is gated per rung by the maintainer.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md section 4", "rationale": "The maintainer directed starting at very small scale to cheaply learn which architectures work, then continuously scaling; the rung boundaries are chosen to reuse the SmolLM2 anchors the programme already measures against and to keep R-0/R-1 inside the free-compute pool documented in docs/next/free-compute-recon.md.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Rung boundaries are bytes-and-cost bands under KOT-SIZE/1 and KOT-COST/1, not parameter counts; the parameter figures are orientation only."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:207:{"id": "ASM-0805", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "The GNN-fusion projection (H-GNN): because the kernel and world layer hold relational data, a graph-neural encoder over that graph, fused into a small LM (soft-token, KV-side, or late fusion), will outperform the same LM given the same graph serialised as text, at matched KOT-COST/1 inference cost. Forward projection: the trained-bridge seam has one replicated positive (E5 adapter) but nsk1 measured text-delivered grounding NET-HARMFUL and internal delivery only echo-grade with integration unresolved, so delivery-without-integration is a live failure mode for any fusion variant.", "backing_ref": "", "resolution_path": "P3-E-GNN-1 (Phase-2, gated on P3-D-GNN and P3-LR-GNN): R-0/R-1 pre-registered test of GNN-encoder fusion vs text-of-graph vs no-graph controls at matched inference cost on a relational-question slice plus the full index for non-regression.", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Never a premise."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:208:{"id": "ASM-0806", "tag": "EXTRAPOLATION", "claim": "The internal-rules projection (H-RULE): building deterministic rule evaluation INTO the model (at one of the five enumerated placements — constrained-decoding head, KV-side memory, adapter, activation steering, dedicated hidden layer) achieves the external verifier-loop's accuracy effect at materially lower inference cost, or higher accuracy at matched cost. Forward projection: the external loop has the programme's one audited end-task efficiency SIGN (f2b-replicate, formal inputs, alignment-confounded), while every measured deep-internal channel is unresolved (nsk1) — no internal placement has any positive evidence yet.", "backing_ref": "", "resolution_path": "P3-E-RULE-1 (Phase-2, gated on P3-D-RULE and P3-LR-RULE): R-1 pre-registered head-to-head of the two cheapest placements (constrained-decoding, KV-side) against the external verifier-loop H-VL at matched accuracy targets, decided on the KOT-COST/1 dual ledger.", "load_bearing": false, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Never a premise."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:210:{"id": "ASM-0808", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Programme-3 inherited-constraint set (design constraints adopted from Programme-1/2 measured negatives, binding on every Programme-3 design): (1) NO real-input or natural-language usefulness claim may be made by any Programme-3 experiment unless its NL front-end has cleared an FK-NLB-3-class gate on the relevant vertical (>=0.90 retention of gold-parse covered exactness AND the S2 dangerous-wrong fail-closed gate), because both measured NL crossings failed (l3a-parse 47.6 percent safe-FAIL, a5-nl 41.6 percent dangerous-FAIL); until then all claims are formal-input-scoped. (2) Every kernel-contribution claim carries the deranged-store and aligned-non-kernel-store controls (the f2b alignment confound). (3) Every coverage number is quoted corpus/rung/kernel-state-indexed only. (4) Compression/membership figures are upper bounds, never achievable savings, until a consumption channel is measured.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md section 7", "rationale": "These are the four failure patterns the feasibility synthesis identified as the walls the previous programme hit (NL boundary, alignment confound, coverage-index stripping, upper-bound inflation); adopting them as hard design constraints is the mechanism by which Programme-3 does not repeat them.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Constraint (1) makes the FK-NLB-3 parser re-entry a shared-infrastructure dependency of Programme-3, not an optional extra."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:211:{"id": "ASM-0810", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Programme-3 revision-2 north-star operationalisation (design choice, post-GPT-5.6 review; supersedes-in-part ASM-0800 items (2)-(4)). (1) W1 is a RESOURCE-CONSTRAINED FRONTIER claim, not a +/-10 percent band claim: at rung R-k a pre-registered budget vector B_k = (max canonically-packed deployment bytes; max p95 latency; max energy/query; max peak accelerator memory + host RSS) is fixed; S must (a) fit within EVERY component of B_k (energy explicitly binds, fixing the revision-1 W1/KOT-COST inconsistency), and (b) exceed EVERY pre-registered, reproducible open comparator and baseline family that fits within every component of B_k - comparators may be smaller or cheaper than S - by margin delta_k on the simultaneous one-sided 95 percent lower confidence bound (per ASM-0813). The full neural/neural-retrieval staircase/Pareto envelope across budgets is published with S plotted against it. The claim a W1 PASS licenses is verbatim 'S exceeds every pre-registered, reproducible open comparator and baseline family searched under budget B_k by >= delta_k on KOT-AI-INDEX/2-vN'; the untestable universal 'higher than all other models of the same size and compute' is retired from every claim surface. (2) 'size' := KOT-SIZE/2, six pinned figures with figure (1) primary: canonically-packed minimally-sufficient artifact bytes (pinned deterministic packing script); compressed distribution bytes (zstd-19); warm resident RAM/VRAM; cold-start working set + bytes read to first answer; index/store construction size + cost; any remote service/cache/corpus dependency (remote bytes count or the smaller-deployment claim is void). The common base image is FROZEN (content-hashed) before any architecture development; anything beyond it counts as the system's bytes. (3) 'inference cost' := KOT-COST/2, a measured RESOURCE VECTOR on pinned hardware under the P3-D-HW protocol: accelerator time + estimated ops; CPU-seconds; bytes read from storage and network; energy (RAPL/NVML, whole-run integration); peak accelerator memory AND host RSS; p50/p95 end-to-end latency; throughput under a pinned concurrency distribution; warm AND cold cache incl. startup/index-load; TTFT and inter-token latency for generative arms; output length controlled or cost-normalised per emitted token. The analytic neural-FLOP ledger is renamed the neural-FLOP DIAGNOSTIC: always reported, never binding, never citable alone as 'compute-matched' (symbolic work enters it at zero, so it is not a compute measure). Methodology borrows MLPerf inference + power discipline (REVIEW-CITED, verified by P3-LR-SYS before freeze). (4) KOT-LIFE/1 lifecycle ledger co-reported with every W1 claim: donor pretraining provenance/compute where known; architecture fine-tune + hyperparameter-search compute actually spent; store authoring/parsing/embedding/indexing/human-review costs; total cost of ownership amortised at 10^3/10^6/10^9 queries (REVIEW-CITED: Sardana et al., verified by P3-LR-SYS). The ledger does not gate W1 numerically (no non-arbitrary common unit) but feeds kill K-P3v2(6). W2 unchanged in objective; its R-2 sweep is conditional on a W1 PASS at R-2 (ASM-0817).", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md sections 1.2-1.4, 2.1; poc/gpt56-review/p3-review-20260711/review.md section 1 + ranked concern 1 + technical error 7", "rationale": "The external GPT-5.6 review demonstrated the revision-1 +/-10 percent bands are gameable (padding into a favourable band, dodging a stronger model just outside it, empty band intersections, losing to a smaller/cheaper dominator), that the neural-FLOP ledger is not a compute measure, that W1 omitted energy while KOT-COST/1 claimed it, that raw bytes without canonical packing are a gaming surface, and that deployment-efficiency comparisons must be lifecycle-priced to be named accurately. Each is accepted and mechanised.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Supersedes-in-part ASM-0800 (its items (2) size, (3) cost, (4) W1 band construction); ASM-0800 item (1) index is superseded-in-part by ASM-0811. Registry is append-only; ASM-0800 line is not edited. Any change to the budget vector composition, packing script, resource-vector membership, or ledger template is a KOT-FAIR version change that re-baselines every comparison."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:213:{"id": "ASM-0812", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Programme-3 revision-2 fair-comparison protocol (design choice; supersedes-in-part ASM-0801). (1) KOT-FAIR/2 opens with a formal resource/baseline THREAT MODEL (P3-D-THREAT): enumerated gaming channels (packaging, band/frontier, cost, index, store, tuning games) x mechanised counters; a channel not counterable at freeze is a documented standing limitation on every claim it touches. (2) FACTORIAL control design spanning content-type x retrieval-architecture x executor, replacing the derangement-centric list (derangement changes alignment and retrieval simultaneously and cannot localise): seed-pinned deranged addressing; label permutation; irrelevant-but-structurally-matched records; edge/relation shuffling for graph arms; aligned-non-kernel store; matched generic-RAG/tool-use control; kernel-as-text null at matched token budget. Each prereg names its cells and what each discriminates. (3) The MATCHED GENERIC NEURAL-RAG / TOOL-USE control is mandatory for any W1 claim: same corpus, same retriever/index, same resource budgets, conventional neural RAG or tool-use architecture - the aligned-non-kernel store does NOT replace it. Standing six-way attribution factorisation: kernel semantics vs structured storage vs retrieval vs deterministic execution vs retry/search vs neural-symbolic integration. (4) Comparator construction by a standing NEURAL FRONTIER-BUILDER (P3-D-FRONTIER): per budget, strongest open models at-or-below budget (pinned name+revision at freeze) + best-effort quantisation/structured-pruning/distillation + neural-retrieval variants + OPTIMISED/ADAPTIVE test-time compute (best-of-k self-consistency alone is too weak; REVIEW-CITED: ICLR-2025 test-time-compute result, verified by P3-LR-RAG) + learned/neural verifiers where budget permits; training-compute-matched from-scratch twins only where the neurosymbolic arm trains from scratch. (5) Tuning symmetry binds on TOTAL tuning compute actually spent (logged into KOT-LIFE/1) with a fixed pre-registered selection rule on a dev split disjoint from the index suite - equal config counts are insufficient. (6) SEALED EVALUATION mandatory for any W1 claim: a secondary suite produced AFTER architecture+store freeze by an independent party or pinned procedural generator, unseen by developing agents, versioned per release; for store-based systems it includes temporally-fresh facts and/or independently held-out domains; a pre-registered frozen-vs-sealed consistency band; a large gap voids the win pending diagnosis. Decontamination screening (n-gram + embedding + human spot-check, win-voiding) remains mandatory but is acknowledged NECESSARY-NOT-SUFFICIENT (misses abstraction-level leakage, error-analysis-driven authoring, sub-threshold paraphrases, donor-weight contamination, researcher adaptation).", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md sections 2.0-2.3; poc/gpt56-review/p3-review-20260711/review.md sections 'Baselines need strengthening' + 'Decontamination is necessary but cannot certify fairness' + ranked concern 5", "rationale": "The review identified the strongest missing control (matched generic RAG over the same corpus/retriever/budgets), showed derangement alone cannot localise what mattered, showed config-count tuning symmetry is not compute symmetry, and showed decontamination screening cannot certify fairness. All accepted and mechanised; the threat model makes the gaming-channel analysis itself a frozen auditable artifact.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Supersedes-in-part ASM-0801 (baseline ladder and controls list). The residual unresolved unfairness channels (closed-corpus contamination, lifecycle incommensurability, baseline-search completeness, residual packaging gaming) are standing limitations stated on every W1 claim, per the corrected section 7.3."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:215:{"id": "ASM-0814", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NL-boundary DEPENDENCY rule (design constraint; strengthens ASM-0808 item (1) from a claims rule to a dependency rule, per the review's ranked concern 3). Every Programme-3 experiment stage whose store is ADDRESSED FROM NATURAL INPUT - verifier-loop NL legs, GNN retrieval from NL queries, KV rule-firing keyed from NL, constrained decoding over NL prompts, H-DD store reinjection on NL tasks, H-PS end-to-end runs - is BLOCKED by the NLB gate (P3-E-NLB-1 clearing 0.90 retention + the S2 dangerous-wrong fail-closed criterion per vertical), OR runs on ORACLE inputs (gold parses / gold subgraphs / gold record addresses) and is labelled 'oracle-diagnostic' in its prereg, licensing NO W1 claim and no real-input claim of any kind. Additionally: (a) P3-D-NLB is itself blocked by the semantic-parsing / program-synthesis / selective-prediction literature review P3-LR-PARSE - the measured parser failure (l3a-parse 47.6 percent retention; a5-nl 41.6 percent + S2 kill fired) is not to be re-attempted with the same approach blind; (b) P3-E-NLB-1, coverage censuses, and G1 computations do NOT wait for index calibration (P3-E-CAL) - they make no index claim and gate everything else.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md sections 0, 3.3a, 4, 5; poc/gpt56-review/p3-review-20260711/review.md sections 'Honesty and programme risks' (NL wall not encoded in dependencies) + section 3 (sequencing) + ranked concern 3", "rationale": "The review showed revision 1 acknowledged the NL wall rhetorically but let GNN retrieval, KV rules, constrained decoding, and H-DD reinjection reach Phase-2 without demonstrated query-to-symbol grounding. The wall is now encoded as blocking edges in the WBS, with the oracle-diagnostic label as the only alternative path, and the parser redesign is lit-review-gated so the measured failure is not repeated.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "MEASURED basis restated within envelopes: l3a-parse FAIL (safe) and a5-nl FAIL (dangerous, S2 fired). The N=2 redesign-cycle bound on NLB attempts lives in K-P3v2(2) (ASM-0818)."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:216:{"id": "ASM-0815", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Design-space amendments (scoping decision; extends ASM-0802). (1) NEW FAMILY H-PS, NL-to-program-synthesis, first-class: parse natural input into a small executable DSL (the kernel's closed grammar or a thin typed layer over it); execute deterministically on the microsecond engine; generate the surface answer FROM the checked result; abstain with CALIBRATED confidence when parse confidence is low (selective prediction; the abstention policy is part of the measured product). Designed by P3-D-PS, blocked by P3-LR-PARSE + P3-LR-NTP; its front-end, if it clears NLB, becomes the shared front-end. Evidence status: cautioned - l3a-parse/a5-nl are its measured-FAIL prior art, which is exactly why it is lit-review-gated. (2) H-RULE corrections: constrained decoding is TRANSPORT, not inference - the engine must have already derived the valid continuation set (H-RULE-CD = engine-derived continuation sets delivered via masking; without the executor it is only an output grammar); KV/bottleneck provenance claims require causal ablation, intervention, or executor traces - attention maps and named units do NOT qualify; the family endpoint vs H-VL is PARETO-FRONTIER dominance over (covered-slice accuracy, coverage reached, p95 latency variance, resource vector), not cost parity alone. (3) H-GNN falsifier rescoped: 'fusion <= text-of-graph on tiny graphs' does NOT kill the family (text is often superior for tiny graphs); the kill is a flat-or-text-favouring curve across a pre-registered subgraph-size x reasoning-depth sweep at matched information and resource budgets, on held-out relation compositions and proof depths; controls = nodes-without-edges, shuffled edges/labels, MLP/DeepSets/plain-Transformer encoders on the same inputs, matched text serialisation, oracle-vs-NL-extracted subgraph (NL leg NLB-gated); four separately instrumented stages: retrieval, graph construction, graph encoding, LM use; endpoint is causal behavioural improvement, never delivery alone. (4) H-GU protocol: >= 3 widths or token budgets; the pre-registered read is the DIRECTION of the interface effect across the sweep (shrinking-to-zero or flat-negative kills; growing-with-scale promotes even from a negative base); variants in scope, each a separate arm: proof-trace distillation, verifier-guided training, synthetic curriculum over rule depth + paraphrase diversity, learned routing, conditional-compute/MoE with a symbolic expert.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md sections 3.2, 3.3, 3.3a, 3.5; poc/gpt56-review/p3-review-20260711/review.md section 2 'Architecture bets' + technical errors 6 and 8", "rationale": "Adopts the review's per-family corrections: the missing program-synthesis design attacks the measured NL wall directly instead of hoping rules emerge in a hidden layer; the CD-as-inference and attention-as-provenance errors are corrected; the GNN and ground-up falsifiers are rescoped so cheap negatives do not over-kill families whose value is scale- or depth-dependent.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Extends ASM-0802's enumeration; the placement-test ordering CD -> KV -> {AD, ACT} -> HL stands. ASM-0805/0806 resolvers are rescoped accordingly (sweep-based kill; Pareto endpoint) without editing those append-only entries."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:218:{"id": "ASM-0817", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Programme-3 gate ladder (design choice; supersedes-in-part ASM-0803's rung-only progression). Every family progresses through five INFORMATION-GAINING GATES, cheapest first, so failures localise: G1 coverage-ceiling - compute Delta_max <= sum_b w_b * kappa_b * (1 - a_b_cov) (w_b = index weight, kappa_b = store-covered fraction of benchmark b's items, a_b_cov = baseline accuracy on covered items); if even perfect covered-item correction cannot reach delta_k the index-mover claim is killed on paper, no GPU (mandatory first step for H-VL, H-RULE, and store-side H-DD; computed in P3-D-POWER). G2 oracle-interface - with gold parses/subgraphs/record addresses, does the mechanism help at all (oracle-diagnostic label, no W1 claim, per ASM-0814); a G2 fail localises to the mechanism. G3 boundary-degradation - how much of G2 survives realistic NL mapping through the NLB-gated front-end, with the P3-D-ORACLE decomposition attributing the loss across parse / retrieval-addressing / execution / generation; a G3 fail localises to the boundary. G4 full-system-vs-frontier - the W1 attempt against F(B_k) with the full framework + sealed eval. G5 scaling - the W1 margin held or improved across >= 2 sizes. Compute rungs R-0..R-4 remain as compute HOMES; promotion requires the current gate's pre-registered primary; a family failing the SAME gate at two consecutive rungs (or failing G1/G2 outright) is closed at scope. SEQUENCING: P3-E-NLB-1, coverage censuses, and G1 computations do not wait for P3-E-CAL; every G4 experiment requires the frozen KOT-FAIR/2 + P3-E-CAL PASS + the G4 block (P3-D-THREAT, P3-D-BASE, P3-D-FRONTIER, P3-D-HW, P3-D-RAGC). W2-CONDITIONALITY (fixing the review-flagged inconsistency): the W2 Pareto sweep inside P3-E-SCALE-2 runs ONLY conditional on W1 passing at R-2; any compression curve produced before a W1 PASS is labelled DIAGNOSTIC, never W2.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md sections 1.4, 3.1, 4; poc/gpt56-review/p3-review-20260711/review.md section 3 'Scaling ladder and cost approach'", "rationale": "The review showed the rung-only ladder lets an architecture fail ambiguously (graph encoder vs retrieval vs NL parse) and that the coverage bound is computable without GPU spend; the gate structure kills failures earlier, localises them, and encodes the review's sequencing corrections (NLB/coverage independent of calibration; W2 conditional on W1).", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Supersedes-in-part ASM-0803 (rung discipline and W2 timing); the rung table, compute homes, and promotion-spend gating in ASM-0803 stand. Given measured external coverage (~0 on external censuses; m0b 0.3542 friendliest-corpus), G1 is expected to bind hard and early - that is its purpose."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:220:{"id": "ASM-0819", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Programme-3 revision-2 work-breakdown structure (process decision; supersedes ASM-0807). PHASE-0 = TEN literature reviews + one direct-design task, all parallel: P3-LR-EVAL (evaluation/AI-index methodology: HELM, composite-index statistics, contamination + sealed-eval practice, proxy-rung validity, benchmark floors/ceilings); P3-LR-SYS (lifecycle cost, MLPerf-style systems benchmarking, storage/I-O economics, energy measurement); P3-LR-RAG (RAG, structured retrieval, knowledge graphs, tool-using neural baselines, adaptive test-time compute); P3-LR-PARSE (semantic parsing, program synthesis, grammar induction, uncertainty/selective prediction); P3-LR-NTP (neural theorem proving, differentiable logic, neural algorithmic reasoning, proof-trace distillation); P3-LR-FUSE (GNN-LLM fusion + neurosymbolic integration survey; absorbs revision-1 P3-LR-NSA + P3-LR-GNN); P3-LR-RULE (rule-injection into transformers); P3-LR-SURG (model compression, dimension/structured pruning, distillation, the exact invariances of transformer model surgery / causal representation analysis); P3-LR-STORE (store authoring/maintenance/provenance + knowledge-update economics); P3-LR-TINY (tiny-model training + small-scale scaling laws); P3-MF-0 (measurement + fair-comparison framework draft). PHASE-1 adds the eight review-named design tasks alongside the family designs: P3-D-THREAT (formal resource/baseline threat model); P3-D-FRONTIER (neural frontier-builder optimising baselines per budget); P3-D-POWER (coverage x max-gain power analysis, the G1 instrument); P3-D-SEAL (independent sealed benchmark); P3-D-RAGC (matched generic-RAG control); P3-D-ORACLE (oracle-to-NL error decomposition); P3-D-HW (hardware repeatability + cold/warm-cache protocol); P3-D-LIFE (lifecycle cost amortisation); plus P3-D-INDEX, P3-D-BASE, P3-D-NLB (now blocked by P3-LR-PARSE), P3-D-PS (new family), P3-D-VL (blocked by P3-D-POWER), P3-D-GNN, P3-D-RULE, P3-D-DD, P3-D-GU. PHASE-2 blocking invariants: every G4/W1-relevant experiment is blocked by the G4 BLOCK = {P3-D-INDEX frozen, P3-D-THREAT, P3-D-BASE, P3-D-FRONTIER, P3-D-HW, P3-D-RAGC, P3-E-CAL PASS}; P3-E-NLB-1, coverage censuses/G1, and oracle-diagnostic G2 stages are EXEMPT from P3-E-CAL; every natural-input store-touching stage is blocked by P3-E-NLB-1 or runs oracle-labelled per ASM-0814; P3-E-DD-1 is blocked by P3-E-DD-0 PASS; P3-E-SCALE-2 requires >= 1 Phase-2 survivor + maintainer gate + the G4 block. Full dependency graph as drawn in the design document section 5. Nothing is created/frozen/run by the design document; the coordinator beads it.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md section 5; poc/gpt56-review/p3-review-20260711/review.md section 4 'Work breakdown'", "rationale": "The review required expanding the lit-review layer (RAG baselines, semantic parsing, theorem proving, model-surgery invariances, lifecycle/systems benchmarking, contamination/sealed-eval statistics, store economics) and named eight missing design tasks; the dependency graph now encodes the NL/coverage wall (ASM-0814), the gate ladder (ASM-0817), and the measurement-first invariant, so the coordinator can bead it directly.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Supersedes ASM-0807. Bead identifiers are design-document names; the coordinator assigns bd ids at creation."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:221:{"id": "ASM-0820", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "KOT-DECOMP/1 stage taxonomy (design choice; the P3-D-ORACLE deliverable, revised per the independent design review of 2026-07-11). (1) Canonical stage superset PARSE (.a intent/frame selection, .b entity/schema linking, .c role/direction binding, .d serialization), RETRIEVE, CONSTRUCT, ENCODE, EXECUTE, RENDER, plus the non-spliceable terminal consumer; every family instantiates an ordered subset; PARSE sub-stages are mandatory wherever a parser exists (the granularity that makes the measured a5-nl PARSE.c mechanism expressible). (2) Per-family boundary set B(F) = the ordered stages whose input regime differs between the family's G2 (oracle-input) and G3 (natural-input) runs; stages outside B(F) are attributed zero by construction. (3) ENCODE is probe-instrumented and splice-limited: a gold encoding of a learned encoder is undefined, so its upstream splice is 'encoder applied to the gold-constructed input' and the encode-vs-use separation comes from the delivery probe versus the endpoint (the nsk1 lesson as instrumentation). (4) TERMINAL RESIDUAL, corrected from the reviewed draft's over-identification: L_term = M_ceiling - M(S, FULL-ORACLE) is NOT identified as LM-use loss; it bundles genuine use/integration failure, irreducible task error and label ambiguity, capacity limits, non-spliceable executor/renderer error, and ceiling misspecification; it is published as an UNATTRIBUTED residual (an upper bound on USE loss); a large L_term with a passing delivery probe is CONSISTENT WITH the nsk1 delivery-without-integration signature and licenses only 'integration-limited (unattributed residual)' language, never 'USE is responsible for X'.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/ORACLE.md sections 3 and 4.4; docs/next/lit/PARSE.md section 8; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dORACLE-20260711/last-message.json ('USE residual is not identified')", "rationale": "The sub-stage granularity is what makes the measured a5-nl ROLE_DIR mechanism a nameable stage; the external reviewer showed the drafted residual claim assigned an unidentified mixture to USE, so the residual is demoted to an explicit upper bound with its confounds named and the claim language barred.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registers the reviewed ORACLE.md draft's proposed ASM-ORC-1 with the review's correction applied. Stage names deliberately avoid the S1/S2 kill-criteria namespace."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:225:{"id": "ASM-0824", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "KOT-DECOMP/1 governance and gate feed (design choice; corrects the review's ranked concern 3 - the reviewed draft invented a FULL-REAL exemption class the design cannot grant itself). (1) sigma = gamma_G3 / gamma_G2 with gamma_G2 = gamma(G2-ANCHOR) and gamma_G3 = gamma(FULL-REAL) per ASM-0821, defined only when the one-sided 95 percent LCB of gamma_G2 > 0; K-P3v2(5)'s 'G2 gain fails to survive G3 at the pre-registered retention margin' is evaluated as UCB95(sigma) < sigma_min with sigma_min set in the family prereg. (2) THE BOUNDARY-DIAGNOSTIC EXEMPTION IS A PROPOSAL, NOT A GRANT: programme rev-2's sequencing exemptions name P3-E-NLB-1, the G1 censuses, and oracle-labelled G2 only; this entry REQUESTS a programme/ASM-0814 amendment creating a boundary-diagnostic class for FULL-REAL runs of this instrument (licensing only the measured retention/sigma/attribution vector - never an index, usefulness, or competitive claim) and bundles the P3-E-CAL sequencing exemption for decomposition runs into the same request; the request has NO EFFECT until an explicit coordinator/maintainer ratification decision is recorded as an amendment. FAIL-CLOSED MEANWHILE: (a) configurations in which every boundary-crossing store-addressing stage is oracled run now as ordinary oracle-diagnostic under ASM-0814; (b) FULL-REAL and partially-real-boundary cells are populated ONLY by replaying frozen, already-measured per-item artifacts of registered runs (no new natural-input execution); a missing artifact excludes that cell with disclosure and never triggers re-execution; (c) any new-family FULL-REAL leg waits for per-vertical NLB clearance or the ratified amendment. (3) KOT-DECOMP/1 SUPPLEMENTS KOT-FAIR/2: the attribution annex is a mandatory co-publication of every G4 attempt by a store-touching family, but it does NOT satisfy or replace KOT-FAIR/2's factorial content-type x retrieval-architecture x executor controls or the matched generic-RAG comparator - those remain separately mandatory. (4) Every configuration with >= 1 oracled stage stays oracle-diagnostic: no W1 claim, no real-input claim of any kind; no oracle number travels unlabelled (claims-lint pattern rider on the shakedown bead). (5) RESOURCE ACCOUNTING: actual CPU/GPU hours of ALL splice runs enter the family's tuning/development audit trail (KOT-FAIR/2 tuning-symmetry ledger); oracle authoring, dual annotation, adjudication, and K-phrasing production hours enter KOT-LIFE/1; any FULL-REAL figure feeding a G4 reading carries the complete KOT-COST/2 warm/cold resource vector, not only cost_us|tokens; 1-2B (R-3) decomposition reruns are explicitly budgeted in the family's R-3 prereg from the gated R-3 allocation, never absorbed silently.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/ORACLE.md sections 7.2, 9, 10; docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md lines 194-201 and 881-889 (ASM-0814/0817 exemption lists); poc/gpt56-review/rev-dORACLE-20260711/last-message.json ranked concern 3 + 'KOT-FAIR/2 and resources'", "rationale": "The reviewer showed the draft's boundary-diagnostic class conflicted with the programme rule that every natural-input store-touching leg is NLB-blocked or oracle-labelled, and that the design was granting itself the exemption; this entry converts the exemption into a ratification request with a fail-closed interim rule, and closes the review's resource-accounting gaps at the governance level.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registers the reviewed draft's proposed ASM-ORC-5, restructured per the review. ASM-0814's W1 prohibition is not weakened anywhere; ratification is a coordinator/maintainer act, not this design's."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:226:{"id": "ASM-0825", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "KOT-DECOMP/1's own falsifier: the P3-E-ORACLE-0 known-answer bars (design choice; corrects the review's ranked concern 2 - the legacy-vertical bars alone were near-tautological). KA-1 (paired ceiling, corrected): FULL-ORACLE reproduces gold-parse covered exactness on the PAIRED NL item slices - 527/527 on the l3a family/world NL slice and 855/855 on a5-nl; the 600/600 figure is the parent FORMAL slice and is checked separately as an engine regression, never as the paired shakedown cell. KA-2 (regression only, disclosed as near-true-by-construction): >= 95 percent of the measured G2-to-G3 loss attributes to the PARSE stage family on both legacy verticals - on this system PARSE is the only boundary-crossing fallible stage, so KA-2 validates plumbing and cannot validate multi-stage causal attribution. KA-3 (with a numeric tolerance, previously deferred): sub-stage attribution on l3a-parse reproduces the measured first-divergence breakdown 228/48/40/41 with each sub-stage's attributed share within +/- 0.10 absolute of the measured share and frame-miss remaining the modal category. KA-4 (bound direction corrected): the S2 rule attributes >= 90 percent of a5-nl's 43 dangerous-wrong events to PARSE.c, AND the PARSE.c repair splice drives the post-repair dangerous-wrong one-sided 95 percent UCB below 0.02 on that vertical - establishing <= 2 percent requires the UCB below the bar; an LB below the bar proves nothing (the S2 KILL direction, LB >= bar, is a different test). KA-5: instrument gates IG-1..IG-5 all pass on the legacy K=1 corpora (disclosed below field practice, shakedown-only). KA-6 (the decisive falsifier, added per review): a SYNTHETIC factorial fault-injection pipeline - deterministic, CPU-only, with a paired control arm and fully known ground truth - containing (a) independently injected faults in >= 2 distinct stages at known marginal rates, (b) one pure two-stage interaction that flips only when BOTH stages are repaired, (c) one harmless artifact divergence (artifact differs from gold, endpoint unaffected), (d) one downstream stage whose apparent (trace-visible) error is caused upstream, (e) planted dangerous-wrong events with known causal stages, (f) one no-effect oracle splice; PASS requires exact recovery of the planted marginal attributions, JOINT (not single-stage) claim language for the planted interaction, zero attribution to the harmless divergence and to the no-effect splice, upstream attribution of the upstream-caused error against the misleading trace label, and 100 percent planted-S2 recovery; the gamma (paired-arm) path runs end-to-end on this pipeline. A FAIL on KA-2, KA-3, KA-4, or KA-6 falsifies KOT-DECOMP/1 (not the architectures) and returns it for redesign before any family G3 run consumes it.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/ORACLE.md section 8; registry/verdicts/l3a-parse.json (parse_stage_breakdown 228/48/40/41; 251/527 retention), registry/verdicts/a5-nl.json (43/855 S2 events); poc/gpt56-review/rev-dORACLE-20260711/last-message.json ranked concern 2 + 'Wrong confidence-bound direction' + 'Incompatible shakedown sample' + 'KA-3 has no actual tolerance'", "rationale": "The reviewer showed KA-2 is nearly true by construction on the legacy verticals and named the exact synthetic-pipeline properties a decisive cheap falsifier needs; KA-6 adopts that list verbatim, and the KA-1/KA-3/KA-4 arithmetic and bound-direction defects are corrected as flagged.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registers the reviewed draft's proposed ASM-ORC-6 with the review's corrections. The shakedown bead P3-E-ORACLE-0 remains a coordinator creation; nothing runs from this entry."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:227:{"id": "ASM-0826", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "KOT-DECOMP/1 statistical specification (design choice; corrects the review-named power and hierarchy defects). (1) Endpoint discipline: each family x vertical names ONE pre-registered endpoint scalar M and always co-reports the selective triple - coverage, selective risk P(wrong | answered), and dangerous-wrong rate. (2) Per-stage risk-coverage curves + AUACC wherever a stage emits confidence; a scalar operating point is never the only view. (3) UNCERTAINTY: paired BCa hierarchical bootstrap on the gamma quantities with the ITEM as the top-level resampling cluster; K phrasings stay nested within their item and are never resampled as independent units; where an LM stage samples (non-greedy), >= 2 registered seeds and seed enters as a registered variance component at its own level. (4) POWER, endpoint-typed (the blanket 'n approx 500-1000 suffices' claim is WITHDRAWN): paired binary endpoints compute McNemar power at the pre-registered target (default: detect stage loss 0.05 at 80 percent power, one-sided 5 percent) from a PRE-REGISTERED discordant-pair-rate estimate sourced from the shakedown or a pilot; required n scales inversely with the discordant rate and can exceed 1000. Continuous endpoints (graph F1, AUACC) use paired-difference power from a pre-registered SD estimate or simulation-based power via the hierarchical bootstrap; McNemar is never applied to non-binary endpoints. The ITEM count is the power unit - K phrasings do not multiply effective n. The legacy 527/855 corpora are measured decision-grade anchors for their own verticals only, not a general sufficiency claim. (5) MULTIPLICITY: sigma is the only gate-feeding estimand and carries the one-sided CI; the stage-loss vectors are diagnostic, receive no FWER correction, and every report states this.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/ORACLE.md section 7; registry/verdicts/l3a-parse.json + registry/verdicts/a5-nl.json envelopes; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dORACLE-20260711/last-message.json ('Power claim is unsupported', 'Stochastic hierarchy is underspecified'); house statistics per ASM-0813", "rationale": "The reviewer showed the drafted power claim was unsupported (McNemar n depends on the discordant-pair rate and does not cover continuous endpoints) and the phrasing/seed hierarchy was unspecified; this entry pins the estimator hierarchy and forces every family prereg to compute its own n from its endpoint type.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registers the statistical half of the reviewed draft's proposed ASM-ORC-2/ORC-5 content, corrected. Complements ASM-0813 (house statistics) without editing it."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:229:{"id": "ASM-0851", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "FRONT/1 F(B_k) semantics, comparator search space, and builder pipeline (design choice; operationalises ASM-0812 clauses i-iii and v). (1) F(B_k) = comparators built from the pinned grid or admitted by nomination, admissible on every MEASURED component of B_k warm and cold, pinned (config/weights/seeds/decoding/index/verifier hashes) at frontier freeze; F(B_k) is content-hashed; any change is a frontier VERSION bump that re-baselines W1 at that rung. (2) ENVELOPE REPORTING: the KOT-COST/2 resource vector is never scalarised - publish the non-dominated set in the FULL resource space plus explicitly named 2-D projections (index x bytes; index x p95 latency; index x peak accelerator memory; index x energy only where the ASM-0850 energy rule makes that dimension binding); dominated and inadmissible points reported, never dropped. (3) STATISTICS INTERFACE: W1 = simultaneous LCB95(INDEX(S)-INDEX(C)) > delta_k over every C in F(B_k), FWER-controlled; NO claim that a max-t procedure loses negligible power however large F is - the comparator covariance is estimated by the hierarchical bootstrap in the pinned analysis plan and P3-D-POWER sizes experiments under the realised |F(B_k)| multiplicity. (4) ENUMERATION: eligibility by measured canonically-packed bytes under the transform grid, never parameter count; S0 may drop a candidate on ANALYTIC bytes only when the estimate exceeds bytes_max x kappa_pack (pre-registered safety factor, proposed 1.25); candidates within the factor are canonically PACKED before any exclusion; all drops logged. (5) GRID: C1 open-weight donors (roster pinned by P3-D-BASE); C2 quantisation ladder (llama.cpp k-quants Q8_0/Q5_K_M/Q4_K_M/Q3_K_M + one pinned calibration int4) applied symmetrically across arms; C2 structured pruning at {12.5,25,50}% ONLY as Minitron-class width(+depth) pruning with KD retraining + teacher correction and Sheared-LLaMA-style recovery-data re-mixing per the landed P3-LR-SURG, with pruned entries OPTIONAL and never load-bearing for a frontier freeze until (a) an R-1 pilot benchmark of the candidate recipe on the actual 135M/160M-class donors passes and (b) the distillation-scaling-law calculation at donor scale (or a KD-vs-continued-pretraining recovery pilot) is done; small-donor caution binding: published big-model retention figures are never extrapolated down; C2 distillation capped by T_k, R-2+ by default; C3 retrieval arms per ASM-0853; C4 adaptive test-time compute per ASM-0852; C5 from-scratch twins only where S itself trains from scratch. Composed R-1 grid is COUNTED, not guessed: ~14 donors x 5 quant levels (incl. none) = ~70 static bases, byte-filtered to ~20-30, x up-to-3 retrieval cells x 2 TTC = <= ~180 composed candidates plus <= ~12 optional pruned/distilled entries. (6) PIPELINE (SEVEN stages S0-S6): enumerate; screen on a pinned ~10% stratified dev mini-suite by successive halving; optimise under ESTIMATED admissibility (bytes measured by packing, latency/energy/memory via a pinned cheap estimator); measure on the P3-D-HW rig; admit on MEASURED figures with a fall-back selection rule (if a family's S2-selected config fails measured admissibility, selection falls back to that family's best admissible logged config, re-measured - never re-opened search); envelope; pin. (7) LEAKAGE + SELECTION: all builder selection on a dev split disjoint from the frozen suite and every sealed release; fixed selection rule = dev-split index restricted to that rung's above-floor components, ties broken by lower measured cost (energy where boundary-admissible, then p95). (8) NL DISCIPLINE: comparators consume natural benchmark text (ASM-0808 applied); no gold parses, subgraphs, addresses or passages; oracle-diagnostic comparators labelled per ASM-0814 never enter F(B_k); the NLB gate binds the kernel front-end only, never the frontier. (9) NOMINATION WINDOW: any party may nominate an open reproducible comparator until freeze; the builder admits it or publishes a one-line refusal reason; post-freeze nominations queue for the next frontier version.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/FRONT.md sections 1.3, 2, 3, 6, 7.2; docs/next/lit/SURG.md section 1; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dFRONT-20260711/last-message.json ranked concern 2 + other-errors list", "rationale": "Turns ASM-0812's frontier clause into an executable, auditable instrument; adopts the external review's named corrections exactly: seven-stage count, packed-bytes-before-exclusion at S0, estimated-screen-then-measured-fallback ordering for S2/S4, full-vector frontier reporting in place of a scalarised cost axis, removal of the unsupported max-t negligible-power claim, counted grid arithmetic, and incorporation of the now-landed P3-LR-SURG recovery recipe and small-model warnings before pruning enters the frozen search space.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registered by the rev-dFRONT-20260711 review revision. Replaces FRONT.md's provisional in-doc id P3F-A2."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:230:{"id": "ASM-0852", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "FRONT/1 adaptive test-time-compute recipe + tuning-compute meter (design choice; operationalises ASM-0812 clause iv and its tuning-symmetry clause; resolves RAG.md sections 7.6/8 OPEN items). (1) AGGREGATION SEMANTICS PER COMPONENT CLASS (class pinned per index component by P3-D-INDEX at freeze; no undefined majority voting): SA short-answer/MC components - agreement = modal share of canonicalised answers under the suite's own pinned normaliser, full ladder P0-P3 eligible; OG open-generation/instruction-following components - majority vote UNDEFINED, the agreement stage is replaced by a pinned mean-logprob confidence proxy, eligible policies are P0 and verifier/PRM-scored best-of-N (P2/P3, the verifier IS the aggregation), self-consistency ineligible; LL LM-loss/perplexity components - deterministic single computation, always P0, TTC does not apply; ABSTENTION emitted only where the index scores an abstention channel, else the P0 answer. (2) LADDER: P0 greedy/single sample; P1 self-consistency N in {4,16,64} adaptive; P2 best-of-N + outcome verifier; P3 PRM-weighted BoN/beam with auto-labels - P2/P3 eligible iff the verifier trains within T_k AND verifier bytes fit bytes_max. (3) Self-charging agreement escalation as the difficulty estimator (n0 = 4 samples, pinned threshold tau; the estimator is stage one of the policy so its compute is charged by construction); base-success~0 fallback to P0 below a pinned floor tau_0. (4) Verifier/PRM training + auto-labelling compute on KOT-LIFE/1, verifier weights on KOT-SIZE/2, verifier inference on KOT-COST/2 - no free component. (5) NON-MATH CALIBRATION GATE per domain x component class before any TTC arm enters a frozen F(B_k): dev-split LCB95(gain over P0) > 0 at that rung or the arm freezes as P0; no published TTC figure is ever assumed to transfer. (6) Full N-sweep decay curves published for every P2/P3 arm. (7) T_k METER: tuning symmetry binds on total tuning compute as a RESOURCE VECTOR T_k = (accelerator-hours, CPU-core-hours), each component separately capped per arm - GPU-hour-only caps left CPU-heavy indexing/search uncapped, corrected here. The unit of an arm is MECHANICAL: a closed ARM TABLE of ledger keys registered at rung entry alongside B_k (R-1 comparator keys: C1-quant, C2-prune, C2-distil, C3-RAG-matched, C3-RAG-free, C4-TTC; a C5-twin key only at rungs where a from-scratch S is live; plus one key for S); every tuning/search/recovery/verifier-training job carries exactly one key before launch; an unattributable job is billed to the largest-spend arm (fail-closed); adding a key after rung entry is a frontier VERSION bump, so family boundaries cannot multiply allowance. Proposed values, maintainer-adjustable and final at KOT-FAIR/2 freeze: T_1 = (4 GPU-h, 40 CPU-core-h) per arm; T_2 = (20 GPU-h, 200 CPU-core-h) per arm; T_3 = (80 GPU-h, 600 CPU-core-h) per arm. An S that spends more than T_k has not won; a comparator arm that exhausts T_k freezes at its best logged config; donor pretraining compute is inherited and declared on KOT-LIFE/1, never netted out and never counted against T_k.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/FRONT.md sections 3.3, 4; docs/next/lit/RAG.md sections 4-8; docs/next/lit/EVAL.md section 7; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dFRONT-20260711/last-message.json ranked concern 2 (caps/units) + other-errors (TTC semantics)", "rationale": "The external review showed the revision-1 meter was not dimensionally closed (GPU-hour caps claiming to cover CPU-hours; vaguely bounded families multiplying allowance) and that majority-agreement TTC semantics were undefined for open generation, instruction following and LM-loss components; the resource-vector cap with a closed mechanical arm table and the per-class aggregation semantics make both executable and auditable.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registered by the rev-dFRONT-20260711 review revision. Replaces FRONT.md's provisional in-doc ids P3F-A3 and P3F-A3-T."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:231:{"id": "ASM-0853", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "FRONT/1 matched-retrieval binding defaults (design choice; resolves RAG.md section 6 OPEN rules 1-5; inherited verbatim by P3-D-RAGC, amendable only by registered change). RULE 1 - one pinned source snapshot per vertical; per-arm indexed objects derived by pinned seed-pinned automated scripts; information parity enforced as four MEASURED checks and no further (source parity, byte-cap parity, decontamination-screen parity, effort disclosure) + the standing residual-asymmetry disclosure carried verbatim on every consuming claim. RULE 2 - CORRECTED per the 2026-07-11 external review: TWO mandatory retrieval cells, BOTH members of F(B_k) whenever S uses a store, each with a distinct claim licence: (a) the SHARED/MATCHED cell - one pinned retriever+index (BM25 + one pinned small dense embedder) over the SAME pinned corpus snapshot at the SAME budgets, over a common text serialisation of every arm's objects - IS the programme's stipulated same-corpus/same-retriever-index/same-budgets control (ASM-0812 clause iii verbatim; KOT-FAIR/2 programme section 2.3 / MF0 section 8.2) and is a REQUIRED member of the W1 control set AND of F(B_k): a W1 claim that has not beaten this cell is void; its structural handicap for arms whose native retrieval is not dense-over-text is DISCLOSED beside its result, never grounds for exclusion; (b) the NATIVE cell - each arm retrieves the way its architecture natively does (kernel addressing for S; the RAG arm's best in-budget retriever) under the same resource budgets - ADDITIONALLY enters F(B_k) as the strongest-system frontier point; it never replaces the shared/matched cell. Every consuming prereg names which cell licenses which sentence. RULE 3 - pinned per rung: max retrieved tokens per query identical across arms, max context length, assembly order = retrieval-score-descending, position-shuffle control cell in RAGC's factorial. RULE 4 - store-vs-store comparisons: identical generator checkpoint, decoding params, retry budget, abstention accounting, tool-executor semantics; tuning <= T_k per arm; the free-corpus whole-system arm is exempt with the narrower better-baseline-exists licence, no attribution licence. RULE 5 - every construction pass booked as build compute in KOT-LIFE/1 and artifact bytes in KOT-SIZE/2 on every arm identically; derivation/construction pipelines content-hash-frozen BEFORE any frozen-suite item is drawn; decontamination screen applies to construction inputs and outputs; a store or index whose construction post-dates suite exposure is VOID for W1 use.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/FRONT.md sections 2.3, 5; docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md section 2.3; docs/next/design/MF0.md section 8.2; docs/next/lit/RAG.md section 6; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dFRONT-20260711/last-message.json ranked concern 1", "rationale": "Revision 1 of FRONT put only the architecture-native cell into F(B_k) and demoted the shared/matched cell to an attribution instrument, contradicting KOT-FAIR/2's binding same-corpus/same-retriever/same-budgets contract; the review's correction is adopted exactly - shared/matched satisfies ASM-0812 and participates in the required W1 control set and the frontier, native additionally enters as the strongest-system point.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registered by the rev-dFRONT-20260711 review revision. Replaces FRONT.md's provisional in-doc id P3F-A4."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:233:{"id": "ASM-0880", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "KOT-FAIR/2 freeze graph (corrects MF0 draft 1's incoherent freeze ownership, GPT-5.6 rev-dMF0 ranked concern 1): the framework freezes only via a dedicated INTEGRATION/FREEZE step P3-D-FAIR, blocked by ALL component designs — P3-D-INDEX (index pins + kot-pack/1 + kot-decon/1 + analysis constants), P3-D-HW, P3-D-LIFE, P3-D-SEAL, P3-D-FRONTIER, P3-D-RAGC, P3-D-THREAT — plus P3-E-CAL PASS and maintainer sign-off. P3-D-INDEX owns only the index piece and does not silently absorb the other components; no G4/W1 experiment or P3-E-CAL execution launches from the MF0 draft.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/MF0.md sections 11-12; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dMF0-20260711/last-message.json concern 1", "rationale": "Draft 1 said P3-D-INDEX freezes the whole framework while its dependency list omitted P3-D-HW/LIFE/SEAL/FRONTIER/RAGC and its freeze conditions required mostly lit inputs rather than completed designs; the review required an explicit integration/freeze bead blocked by all component designs.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registered by the MF0 draft-2 revision (GPT-5.6 review rev-dMF0-20260711 applied); fresh ASM-0880..0909 block, append-only. Renumbered twice pre-citation: three concurrent Phase-1 review-revision writers collided on the 0820 block and the FRONT/1 revision holds 0850+."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:234:{"id": "ASM-0881", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "W1 resource admissibility (corrects MF0 draft 1's non-binding 'full resource vector', rev-dMF0 ranked concern 2): B_k has PRIMARY components (max canonically-packed serving bytes; max p95 service-time latency, plus max p95 latency under the pinned open-loop load where an offered-load claim is made; max energy/query at the declared boundary; max peak accelerator memory + host RSS) and HARD SECONDARY CEILINGS registered in the same prereg on every other measured KOT-COST/2 component (CPU-seconds/query, accelerator-time/query, bytes read from storage+network/query, TTFT/TPOT for generative arms, min throughput under pinned load), set generously (draft 3x the strongest fitting comparator) to exclude resource laundering; exceeding ANY ceiling is inadmissible. ENERGY: a W1 run executes on ONE common platform for all arms with a common measurable energy boundary at which energy binds; if no measurable boundary exists the claim must carry the explicit ENERGY-EXCLUDED label on its claim surface, never a silent drop. ADMISSIBILITY UNDER UNCERTAINTY: membership of F(B_k) and S's own admissibility are decided on UCB95 of each measured resource component over the repeatability repetitions, fail-closed when the UCB straddles a ceiling.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/MF0.md sections 4.1, 8.1; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dMF0-20260711/last-message.json concern 2 + 'Resource admissibility ignores measurement uncertainty'", "rationale": "Draft 1's B_k constrained only bytes/p95/energy/memory while KOT-COST/2 recorded more, so a system could consume far more CPU/IO/network/accelerator work and still win W1; dropping energy whenever unmeasurable contradicted the parent's 'energy explicitly binds' W1; point-estimate membership made frontier composition unstable near ceilings.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registered by the MF0 draft-2 revision (GPT-5.6 review rev-dMF0-20260711 applied); fresh ASM-0880..0909 block, append-only. Renumbered twice pre-citation: three concurrent Phase-1 review-revision writers collided on the 0820 block and the FRONT/1 revision holds 0850+."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:243:{"id": "ASM-0890", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Generic-RAG comparator equity rule (rev-dMF0 'the generic-RAG control remains under-specified', consuming the landed RAG.md): the frontier clause (iii) comparator is built from the SAME pinned source-evidence snapshot under the SAME byte/build/query budgets as the kernel arm, but NOT necessarily the kernel's own retriever/index — forcing a specialized retriever onto a conventional RAG baseline can structurally handicap it, and 'same source snapshot' is not 'same retriever' (converting one snapshot into passages vs records vs triples indexes different objects). The RAG comparator is implemented from a pinned STANDARD harness (FlashRAG-style, release pinned), with both BM25 and dense retriever cells mandatory, retrieval recall@k reported separately from end-task accuracy, and identical index-bytes/build-compute/query-compute ledgers on both arms; the identical-vs-architecture-specific retriever decision is made per factorial cell by P3-D-RAGC under FRONT/1 section 5's binding default rules.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/MF0.md section 8.2; docs/next/lit/RAG.md sections 3 and 6; docs/next/design/FRONT.md section 5; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dMF0-20260711/last-message.json", "rationale": "Draft 1 inherited the parent's 'same corpus, same retriever/index' phrasing, which the landed RAG review shows can handicap the conventional baseline; the literature supports equal source evidence + equal budgets + a pinned standard implementation, with retriever-architecture parity decided per cell.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registered by the MF0 draft-2 revision (GPT-5.6 review rev-dMF0-20260711 applied); fresh ASM-0880..0909 block, append-only. Renumbered twice pre-citation: three concurrent Phase-1 review-revision writers collided on the 0820 block and the FRONT/1 revision holds 0850+."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:244:{"id": "ASM-0891", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "Factorial attribution controls are FRAMEWORK-owned and specified in MF0 section 8.5 (rev-dMF0 'the parent's mandatory factorial content x retrieval x executor controls are mentioned but never actually specified'): the cell inventory restates programme doc section 2.2(2) verbatim — (a) seed-pinned deranged store-to-item addressing, (b) label permutation within records, (c) irrelevant-but-structurally-matched records, (d) edge/relation shuffling for graph arms, (e) aligned-non-kernel store, (f) matched generic-RAG/tool-use comparator plus BM25/dense/position-shuffle/random-document cells, (g) kernel-as-text null at matched token budget — organised on the content-type x retrieval-architecture x executor axes, each cell annotated with what it discriminates. The EXECUTOR axis, which the parent names without enumerating, gets two DRAFT cells owned here: engine-on vs engine-off (same store, execution disabled) and generic-executor substitution where meaningful; P3-D-RAGC/P3-D-ORACLE freeze them. Every Phase-2 W1-relevant prereg NAMES which cells it instantiates and what each discriminates; the full cross product is never mandatory, the named-cells rule is.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/MF0.md section 8.5; docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md section 2.2; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dMF0-20260711/last-message.json concern 1", "rationale": "The review found the mandatory factorial controls were referenced but never specified in the framework document; the framework must own the specification so individual experiments cannot re-derive (and quietly weaken) it, and the executor axis needed at least draft cells to be instantiable.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Registered by the MF0 draft-2 revision (GPT-5.6 review rev-dMF0-20260711 applied); fresh ASM-0880..0909 block, append-only. Renumbered twice pre-citation: three concurrent Phase-1 review-revision writers collided on the 0820 block and the FRONT/1 revision holds 0850+."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:246:{"id": "ASM-0861", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "P3-D-POWER metric-type and family-eligibility contract. (1) METRICS: the itemwise perfect-correction functional kappa*(1-a_cov) is registered for itemwise-accuracy metrics ONLY (the chance/ceiling normalization transform is itself defined only for accuracy-type metrics, per the EVAL review); every index component with any other metric type (loss, logprob, generation-scored, calibration, ...) receives full headroom W_b*cap_b until a per-metric maximum-gain functional with a registered score range is added \u2014 it is never forced through the accuracy formula and never dropped. The index pin MUST declare metric_type per component; the rig fails closed without it. (2) FAMILIES: Form A may be applied to a mechanism family only with a REGISTERED noninterference/covered-support argument (behaviour on uncovered items identical to baseline; entire incremental benefit requires a covered, correctable item), cited via family_eligibility.noninterference_ref in the census input. Plausible for fail-closed verify/retry (H-VL) and executor-derived masking with fail-closed fallback (H-RULE-CD) but NOT established for KV injection, adapters, train-time program-synthesis variants, or H-DD weight surgery, which may change uncovered behaviour or transfer knowledge globally: those get no free kill and no free pass from this rig until they carry their own registered argument or a different ceiling design.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/POWER.md sections 1.2, 1.2a; poc/gpt56-review/rev-dPOWER-20260711/last-message.json 'Other substantive gaps' items 1-2; docs/next/lit/EVAL.md section 6 (accuracy-only transform)", "rationale": "The review flagged that revision 1 asserted Form A covers all store-dependent families and all index metrics without support. A mechanism with off-coverage or global effects can exceed the covered-item bound, and non-accuracy metrics have no chance floor or analogous verified transform, so applying the accuracy functional to either would be an invalid generalization that can false-kill. Restricting the functional's registered scope and requiring explicit eligibility arguments keeps the ceiling an actual upper bound.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Proposed bead P3-D-ELIG authors the eligibility references. SUPPORTED_METRICS=('accuracy',) in power.py is the registered functional list; extending it is a design change requiring a new ASM or an amendment."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:251:{"id": "ASM-0900", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB/1 role and scope (P3-D-NLB, bead kernel-of-truth-s55r.13, the FK-NLB-3 re-entry). (1) NLB is the shared GATE INSTRUMENT for the natural-language boundary: P3-E-NLB-1 must clear the joint G-NLB gate (ASM-0901) PER VERTICAL before ANY natural-input store use by any family (ASM-0814 verbatim); the two verticals gate independently (the FK-NLB-1 precedent). (2) The front-end under test is NLB-FE/1, a TWO-TIER parser+abstention SYSTEM: Tier-0 = repaired deterministic template/trie fast path (exact-match acceptance only, ROLE_DIR-repaired, fail-closed on ambiguous orientation); Tier-1 = a small learned parser (<=360M) under grammar-constrained decoding with a contract-and-contrast acceptance layer and a frozen selective-prediction threshold. (3) Fail-closed invariants, frozen as design law: the deterministic engine is the SOLE answer authority; the parser is an UNTRUSTED PROPOSER; no surface answer is emitted except from an engine execution of an ACCEPTED parse; any input failing acceptance (either tier) yields ABSTAIN or CLARIFY, never a guessed answer; the whole risk-coverage curve is the measured product and the shipped operating point is one frozen threshold on it. (4) The instrument makes NO index claim: P3-E-NLB-1 is exempt from P3-E-CAL and the G4 block per the programme sequencing exemption; a G-NLB PASS licenses ONLY the unblocking of NL store legs, never a W1 or usefulness claim.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/NLB.md sections 1, 3; docs/next/programme-3-neurosymbolic-architecture.md sections 0 (ASM-0814), 4, 5; docs/next/lit/PARSE.md sections 0, 8", "rationale": "The measured NL-boundary FAILs (l3a-parse 47.6 percent retention, a5-nl 41.6 percent + S2 fired) were produced by a verbatim-lexicon no-learning front-end; the PARSE lit-review's net judgement is capability-limited-as-leading-hypothesis with the strongest matched-accounting recipe being fine-tuned-small-parser + grammar-constrained decode + calibrated abstention, and the two-tier microsecond/millisecond shape is the cost envelope the review recommends designing first. Making the engine the sole answer authority and the parser an untrusted proposer is the direct structural answer to the a5-nl wrong-with-provenance failure.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Fresh block ASM-0900-0919 opened for P3-D-NLB; 0907-0919 remain free. Registered by docs/next/design/NLB.md."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:252:{"id": "ASM-0901", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "G-NLB, the exact P3-E-NLB-1 success gate, per vertical, all clauses jointly required. (1) RETENTION: retained covered exactness (engine-exact answers on covered scored items under blind NL phrasing, over the gold-parse ceiling of the SAME items) must have one-sided 95 percent lower confidence bound >= 0.90; FAIL fires when the upper bound < 0.90; between = INCONCLUSIVE (the l3a-parse three-way shape retained). (2) S2 SAFETY, defined precisely as UNCONDITIONAL risk: P(answered AND wrong) over covered scored items; gate leg UB95 < 0.02; kill leg LB95 >= 0.02 (the a5-nl S2 shape retained); the SELECTIVE risk P(wrong | answered) is a mandatory CO-REPORT (the two diverge exactly when coverage drops) but the binding bound is unconditional, because retention already punishes over-abstention. (3) STRATUM SAFETY: every directional frame x orientation stratum with pre-registered minimum support carries a near-zero wrong allowance (stratum kill boundary pinned at freeze from the power arithmetic); an aggregate pass with a failing directional stratum is a FAIL. (4) CREDITABLE ABSTENTION: items independently annotated ambiguous/unanswerable BEFORE scoring are scored correct on ABSTAIN/CLARIFY and wrong on any answer; they sit outside the retention denominator and inside the safety accounting. (5) STATISTICS: with K>1 phrasings per base query, all intervals are cluster-robust over base queries (pre-registered cluster bootstrap); exact integer boundaries recomputed and pinned in the frozen record before any scored run (the l3a-parse boundary-pinning precedent); S1 control fail-closed rides in the same Holm family as S2, per the parent instruments. (6) PER-VERTICAL: family/world and code gate independently; clearing one vertical unblocks NL store legs on THAT vertical only.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/NLB.md section 4; registry/verdicts/l3a-parse.json; registry/verdicts/a5-nl.json; docs/next/lit/PARSE.md section 8 requirements (1)-(7)", "rationale": "The PARSE gate-instrument requirements demand an exact S2 definition (unconditional vs selective diverge under falling coverage), pre-specified sample-size/confidence rules, systematic-error strata with near-zero allowances rather than average risk, and creditable abstention on annotated ambiguity; retaining the parent instruments' Wilson/Holm shapes and three-way reading keeps the successor commensurable with the measured FAILs it re-enters.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Consumed by K-P3v2(2)/(5) (ASM-0818) and by every ASM-0814 NL-leg unblock. Boundaries are pinned at prereg-freeze by the mechanical analysis script, never post hoc."}
registry/assumptions.jsonl:253:{"id": "ASM-0902", "tag": "STIPULATED", "claim": "NLB-EVAL/1, the gate corpus protocol, per vertical. (1) BASE ITEMS: the frozen covered scored query sets of the parent instruments (l3a 527 over 7 in-scope families; a5 855) plus matched control sets; shape-ambiguous families stay carved out per the parents. (2) PHRASINGS: K=3 blind held-out phrasings per eval query (upgrading the parents' K=1, which was below field practice), authored under the parents' blind fresh-identity protocol. (3) FOUR-WAY SEPARATION with DISJOINT SOURCES: TRAIN (synthetic grammar-recombination paraphrases + canonical templates over fresh identities only - no eval query, no blind corpus, no eval author-source), DEV/model-selection (designer-authored fresh identities), CAL (calibration + threshold selection: author-source S1 over a pre-registered ~40 percent query split), EVAL (final: DISJOINT author-source S2 over the remaining ~60 percent, authored AFTER the front-end pin). (4) FREEZE ORDERING, hash-witnessed: train and pin parser weights + grammar mask -> author CAL -> select and freeze threshold -> pin the full front-end content-hash -> author EVAL blind -> single scored run. (5) ADVERSARIAL STRATA: both orientations of every directional frame at pre-registered minimum support per orientation per source; a Dr.Spider-style perturbation suite (synonym / structure / typo-noise) with per-perturbation worst-case reported; an independent ambiguity/answerability annotation pass before scoring; the descriptive no-label synonym probe retained. (6) INSTRUMENT VALIDITY: the parents' phrasing-corpus lints + recoverability audit gate (>= 0.95 strict recovery by a human/LLM auditor from the phrasing alone, else the corpus, not the parser, is repaired) apply to every authored set. (7) LEGACY CORPORA: the committed K=1 l3a-parse/a5-nl phrasing corpora are DIAGNOSTIC-ONLY forever after (outcomes are public in verdicts); no successor gate may score on them and no parser may train on them.", "backing_ref": "docs/next/design/NLB.md section 5; docs/design-nl-boundary-l3a-parse-a5-nl.md sections 4-5 (FK-NLB-8/9 + recoverability gate); docs/next/lit/PARSE.md sections 6.5, 8", "rationale": "K=1 single-source phrasing was the parents' weakest instrument property; the PARSE review requires K>1 disjoint-source phrasings, four-way data separation, both-orientation directional tests, perturbation suites, and independent ambiguity annotation, and the conformal/calibration literature voids any guarantee under undisclosed phrasing-source shift - source-disjoint CAL vs EVAL makes the shift stress measurable instead of silent. The freeze ordering generalizes the parents' pin-before-authoring discipline to a learned front-end.", "load_bearing": true, "status": "open", "owner": "designer-1", "date": "2026-07-11", "notes": "Corpus sizes: ~1,581 scored phrasings (l3a) and ~2,565 (a5) at K=3 before strata additions; exact counts and boundaries pinned at freeze."}
